i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:

Note that the signaling at this intersection adds to the confusion, as there are two traffic lights ~200 feet apart for two different intersections.  For this incident, the vehicle stopped at the second red light after running the first red light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Arrived at crosswalk just when countdown timer started.  Aggressive driver ran the red light missing me by inches as I tried to enter the crosswalk.  With 15 seconds remaining on the countdown, dozens of vehicles in both directions continued to run the red light without slowing or stopping, refusing to yield to me as I tried to enter the crosswalk.  I was unable to cross.

This is an incredibly dangerous intersection, as drivers simply do not stop for the light.  HAWK crossings are deadly.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Once again... folk coming up Allesandro and not stopping at the stop sign. Happens way to frequently. This morning a Jeep Grand Cherokee actually accelerated as they approached the stop sign (I only heard them due to the blind corner) with me starting through the intersection (someone coming up from the canyon actually performed a proper stop and let me have my turn to cross through the intersection as I was stopped first).
Intersection might be the most dangerous part of my ride.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a very narrow 2-lane road and yet I was passed by an 18-wheel TRACTOR TRAILER on this road and was almost hit. The truck refused to move over and not only is there no bike lane on this stretch road there is almost nothing of a shoulder. There is no law against this truck being on this road, and I think it was there to take a shortcut to one of our many distribution warehouses. Takeaway, be careful riding this road on weekdays in the early mornings; only weekENDs from now on.

A bicyclist died after a collision with a car early Tuesday morning along Highway 126 in Piru. 

The California Highway Patrol received a call of the incident between a bicyclist and a white, four-door sedan on westbound Highway 126 east of Main Street in Piru at approximately 5:45 a.m. on Tuesday.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

details:
Dog ran onto bike path through 
Opening in fence causing swerve and crash

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Group of riders nearly missed a walker who was not paying attention. The lack of a bike lane in a location that clearly has high demand for one, as well as space for one is a clear and present danger for all involved.

i_type: Fall
details: almost fell because got blindsided by other bikers while turning

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: The people crashed into each other

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: sharp left turn caused my friend to go over the line and crash into a pedestrian

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking to class when someone 2 bikes ahead of me stopped in the roundabout (there was no need to yield). I was able to stop in time to avoid collision, but the person behind me did not and ran into me.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was biking from work to class and a biker came from between the library and ILP (during construction phase) and cut me off. I hit my brakes to avoid collision (unable to swerve due to pedestrians), barely missing their back tire and flew over my handlebars. I had severe scrapes and swelling on my face, hands, and arms with bruises on my legs. 

Bring back the bike path between the library and ILP to avoid this!

i_type: Fall
details: witnessed another collision at this roundabout. Too much traffic.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crashed into someone passing me at the roundabout

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: One person in front of me was on a e-scooter at the roundabout, one other person who was crossing the bike path while operating her phone did not see this person coming. They were about to collide but the person on e-scooter somehow managed to hard brake, I was about to hit him too because I was too close to him and was unprepared.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking home from class when the horizontal bike rider didn't acknowledge that people are also coming out of pardall tunnel. Honestly this is why I hate biking here, it's like people think cars are different than bikes. Plus, it's harder to stop and go on a bike. No signage = free for all.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Turning left under an underpass

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I hit someone with my bike but we were both ok.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I see a lot of near-misses at this intersection caused by bicyclists making turns

i_type: Fall
details: I was biking and I changed gears, but then my chain slipped off, then the gear ended up cutting into my leg. It was horrific.

i_type: Fall
details: There was a girl who was exiting the bike rack area on her bike. There is a lot of foot-traffic in the area, and she fell while avoiding a pedestrian walking in front of her.

i_type: Fall
details: Not entirely sure what happened, but all of a sudden I was on the ground. I'm thinking I must've hit the curb at the wrong angle, and the bike came out from under me. I've never had a fall before, so really not sure what it could've been other than the loose gravel or curb. The angle and curve of this particular spot has always seemed a little sketchy to me and now I've learned the hard way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car rolled stop sign as turning left and did not see me passing the intersection…swerved right at top gear to avoid and fell in my right side breaking my clavicle

i_type: Fall
details: Rider lost control at bottom of hill, possibly broke arm.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: collision area

i_type: Fall
details: I lost control of my bike as I attempted to bring my from my right hand to my left. Consequently, my bike’s handles jolted to the left and I lost control. Stumbling, I almost left unscathed but my own bike tripped me and I fell violently to the pavement, causing cuts to my hand and elbow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Too many reckless people continuously riding their e-bikes illegally on the sidewalk with pedestrians.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
riding on a main artery street, entered a T-intersection, where a minor street runs into the main street, a van turned left from the main street into the minor street, and broadsided me on the left side.  
Tendon and ligament damage to both knees and shoulders, torn meniscus in one knee, labrum tear in one shoulder.

i_type: Fall
details: Fall caused by root bump in road surface.  Numerous broken bones, ambulance ride, eight day hospital stay

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Turning left on San Andres heading west on Anapamu is incredibly dangerous. Cars speed on San Andres (way above the 25MPH speed limit) and visibility and yield compliance is terrible due to parked cars. I just get off  my bike now and walk across this intersection because it is so sketchy

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A black suv was turning left out of the long driveway here. It didn't see me and I was going too fast to stop completely. I slowed and my bike went into their front left wheel well. I don't remember how but i fell/ was forced off my bike and thrown onto the road. The drivers then drove around me and left. A guy wearing a cardigan came and checked on me (Thank you cardigan guy) and called the SBPD who then drove me and my bike home.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car tailed me aggressively when I took the lane and then dangerous swerved around me and cut me off while biking on San Andres. People drive very fast and aggressive on this street and there are no bike lanes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was BOOKING towards carrillo on my ebike  (~20 mi/hr) and a car aggressively swerved around me at 40+mi/hr. San Andres between Micheltorena and Carrillo is a death trap for cyclists. People fly through this section with no regard for the many pedestrians and people on bikes. If it's not the crazy drivers it's the buses or cars pulling out of blind driveways that will take you out. Something needs to happen here. It's even sketchier at night.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Barriers in the road have created a very confusing point for cyclists and pedestrians here. Pedestrian stepped out into road directly in front of me while greeting his friend. I was proceeding through the intersection up State Street with a green light. Pedestrian was knocked to the ground. I saved it, but not before running the side of my front wheel against the curb. Cosmetic damage. 

The city needs to resolve those barriers and make the traffic patterns clearer.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Riding in bike lane, car traffic backed up due to Lacrosse Tournament, and cars were not moving, person opened passenger front door of Lincoln Navigator to let daughter out, just as I was approaching driver side door.  Head first into door, launched off bike.  Broke collar bone and neck injury.  Person explained they did not want daughter to be late and did not see me riding along bike path.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bike lane not clear due to parked cars

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I forgot to signal while turning into my apartment complex and another cyclist hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going down the hill from campus to Goleta beach. As I approached the pump house a bike came flying out directly in front of me — I fully braked and I missed him by inches. Fortunately, I know that people sometimes ride irresponsibly (especially e-bikers) and I was on the watch. It happened so fast and scared me very much because I could've been going at least 20 mph down that hill. The biker simply sprinted away like nothing happened.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Biking to school and almost hit someone who I assume did not hear my bike bell.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding my bike crossing a small intersection where we had the right of way and the car thought they were faster than me and decided to go and basically hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Saw a car making a right turn and nearly avoided someone on a bike crossing the street. The crosswalk had the light to go safely but car didn’t pay attention to it

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: No injury

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: They bumped into eachother

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The other cyclist was on his phone therefore not watching the road and he crossed the yellow line riding on my side… and it was dark so I didn’t see him coming at me.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Driver parked on path

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bringing my child home in the bike trailer. Confusing right turn area for cars there.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling south on State Street then a group of pedestrians all looking at their phones crossed against the light. I shouted at them “Hey, please look up” and they did and I missed them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: two teenagers - one on ebike the  other running behind him - were moving quickly down the spiral ramp and almost hit me head first. closely avoided crash but there's almost nothing I could do as they came around the corner fast

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: footbridge is steep with blind curves and i nearly crashed head on with another bike coming down the ramp from downtown too fast

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Riding in bike lane and man opened his car door as I was passing. Had to move from lane to avoid being hit.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car turning right onto De La Vina hit a bike going straight

i_type: Fall
details: I was riding on the no car zone of State Street and a teenager made a sharp turn right next to me without looking. I hit the breaks hard to avoid hitting him and consequently went over the handlebars.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I witnessed a rider on a BCycle coming south on the sidewalk on de la vina street. Approaching the intersection at Anapamu he rang the bell to alert a pedestrian (an older man) who was on the corner, and they nearly collided. The pedestrian was adamant that the rider shouldn’t have been on the sidewalk but the rider escalated and followed the man for two blocks shouting angrily at him and the man shouted back and the rider pulled a knife out of his pocket

i_type: Fall
details: L just fell

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
With the new plastic pillar separating the bike lane from the cars, cars have been driving faster than before.
Also, everytime I'm going up the bridge on my non electric bike, I'm getting passed by electric bike. However, because of the plastic pillars, electric bikes that pass me have to go on the road.
Those new plastic pillars make this bridge way more dangerous than before.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: People are always biking on the sidewalk across this bridge. There is a class 2 bike lane on the bridge but clearly many people don't feel comfortable using it, so they ride on the sidewalk which causes problems with pedestrians. Maybe some more separation between the bike lane and cars with wider paint and plastic bollards would work.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling east on Haley in bike lane truck made right hook onto Laguna from the left lane ! I swerved into the curb just missing getting t boned

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Saw someone get doored biking down San Andres St.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Skilled and competitive group ride was struck by unassociated "cyclist" riding carelessly on an ebike as he tried to overtake the group and sideswiped me. Several cyclists were injured, and several bikes incurred thousands in damages. 

https://m.imgur.com/a/YyU50Lk

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was training for the Santa Barbara sprint triathlon coming back from butterfly Beach on Channel Drive. I waited at the stop sign for several cars to go by and then started to make my turn left. As I was turning onto Cabrillo Blvd., a car that was at the stop sign by the bird refuge decided to proceed with her left hand turn towards Montecito and run into me. Luckily she had been at a full stop and  was just accelerating. Although I was thrown over my handle bars and my bike was destroyed.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a 5 point stop sign. Cars are often distracted with their turn to go instead of looking out for bicycles.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is one of the most notorious spots on the coastal bikeway. I was turning into the bike path and made sure no cars were behind and signaled as well. A car then sped around to pass me and merge into the interstate almost hitting me. Also the stop sign is not always observed.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While in the bike lane and attempting to turn left to the bike path, I was struck by a driver.  I checked and thought the intersection was clear and signaled well in advance of the turn.  The driver passed the car that was immediately behind me, accelerating through the intersection and struck me with her right front fender.  The driver was driving too fast and too aggressively (according to witnesses), and reported that she did not see me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Speeding car and walking my bike across intersection. Super scary and unsafe crossing when biking or walking.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going straight through a light and the oncoming car was turning left and didn’t stop and almost hit me in the intersection. I had to hop off my bike and walk out of the intersection. It was dusk but I had my lights on.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling westbound on Anapamu Street crossing state, and pedestrians crossed against the light, and I nearly crashed with them. I rang my bell, and shouted, “watch out!” and they moved out of the way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As I was approaching Chapala on anapamu Street, a car zoomed up from behind me, so if they could turn left as the light changed. I had to use my brakes and shout at the man who did not respond.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Near misses in this area have occurred more than once for me at this particular roundabout. This particular incident I had to fall onto the curb as I did not have time to clip out… this woman was texting on her phone and did not even look up or see what had happened until other cars honked at her after seeing me fall. Almost all of these times have been near missed due to cell phone use or people not looking out for bikers. I am extremely cautious, never take risks while bikingand always signal.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was traveling southwest bound on the Cota St separated bikeway. A vehicle stopped in the southwest bound vehicle travel lane. As I came upon the vehicle, passengers disembarking opened the car door which swung  and hit my handlebar directly (or from behind) knocking me away from the vehicle. I hit the top of my head on the corner of the curb (I was wearing a helmet) and my body fell in the mud with the bike on top of me. (The driver and passengers got out to check if I was ok.)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Sight lines are bad for cars intersecting this portion of the bike route. Car turning left WB couldn't see me from the stop sign and turned into the road but we both slowed down in time to avoid collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Biking in the NW direction on Laguna St, which doesn’t have a stop sign. Vehicles at the intersection on East Cota do have a stop. As I passed the county yard, A vehicle passed me headed NW which partially obstructed a pickup truck’s view of my bike. The Pickup truck was headed NÉ on East Cota. Driver in pickup seemed in a rush and rolled through the stop sign and nearly hit me and Driver sped off in the NE direction.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking and there was a car on the right shoulder stationary , I moved to the left side to pass it. Then with no warning it does an illegal u turn and I hit it broadside.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I'm not sure of the exact stage but here is what I saw:
A woman on a bike was on the ground close to a car that was turning from mission westward to San pascual.
I think the bike was riding on mission eastward
With the usual traffic on mission st at San Pascal st, a stopped car on the left lane eastward on mission street let the car that wanted to turn left on San pascual. The turning car didn't see the bike and the bike hit the car
The woman was sitting along the car, people tending for her

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This route is marked as a crosstown bicycle route, but to connect with Modoc you need to cross this busy intersection and turn left. Visibility is terrible, especially because cars are often backed up to get on the highway. A marked crosswalk or bike crossing lights might be helpful.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling southbound on State Street at about 15 miles an hour, and the bike in front of me started weaving back-and-forth really wide. I shouted to him straight line straight line, and he stopped weaving.

i_type: Fall
details: There is a metal grate in the bike lane at the stop sign heading west on State at the Arlington intersection. I witnessed a rider get a tire stuck in the grate which caused them to slip and fall when slowing down for the stop sign. They were fine, but the bike lane is not a good place for this design of grate.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Turned right from bike path onto Storke bike lane. Hit from behind by vehicle.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Friend was biking ahead of me going N on the bike path. We stopped and looked both ways before crossing Mesa rd, but a car came flying up to the stoplight in the right turn lane (to turn right on los Carneros) and my friend didn't see it until we yelled. The bike and car collided slightly, but both managed to stop before a bad collision happened. There were cars waiting at the light to go straight which blocked our view of the cars in the turn lane and blocked cars' view of us crossing. Scary.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Biking home in the dark with a light, vehicle turned in front of me and I had to break and swerve right to miss the car.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: An e-bike came barreling around the corner and I thought that we were going to collide. He was going way too fast.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Coming from Phelps road headed west across the intersection towards the Ellwood trails. Car turning left off Cannon Green Drive rolled stop sign, causing me to brake hard to avoid collision. Cars regularly run this stop sign if they don't see a car.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling northbound at the bend of James Fowler Rd and Fairview Ave in the bike lane with my bike lights on. A vehicle heading southbound on Fairview at this intersection turned left heading into the neighborhood and struck me. I was thrown from my bike and landed on my head. Fortunately I was wearing a helmet but still received a concussion that has left me with dizziness and imbalance for the past 14 months in addition to a torn MCL left knee and broken ribs. The bike was totaled.

i_type: Fall
details: I was headed toward UCSB on the Los Carneros bike path. It was dark and the oncoming traffic lights were blinding. I started to drift to the side of the bike path. I hit a bush, and fell off my bike.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: 2 pedal bikes, one in the wrong lane of bike path collided. There was a branch obstructing their view. Rider that was in his lane was the one injured

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was turning right onto Hollister leaving the farmers market, vehicle turning left from Hollister made an illegal u turn while I had right of way/a green right turn light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While biking along Hollister, a delivery truck almost backed up out of the alleyway behind the stores on the E end of Storke Plaza into the bike lane while I was passing. The driver had their window down and stopped about a foot away from my bicycle when it became clear that they were not stopping and I yelled at them that I was there.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car turning right onto the freeway ramp did not seem to have object permanence about the bike (me) that they had just passed coming down the hill, or they just assumed that they had the right of way to turn across the bike lane onto the ramp without looking. I hit the breaks and yelled, but they continued turning. Another car was preparing to follow behind the first car and turned, but they heard me yell and stopped to let me pass before turning. Scary intersection and I'm extra careful there.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle turning right onto 101 onramp, did not check blind spot and I had to slam on brakes to avoid being hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A young rider on a fat tire e-bike passed me but then pulled in very quickly, cutting me off.  I had to brake hard to avoid hitting him.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A bike rider was knocked off her bike when a car didn't allow enough space for her between a parked car and his car. The car's side mirror was broken by the impact. The cyclist was responsive and didn't hit her head, but I don't know how serious the injuries to her arms and legs were.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bike lane becomes car parking after 6pm on this road, so I took the lane since it was super dark and I was not in the mood to be doored. Car came up from behind me and was angry that I was in the lane, so they proceeded to go around me at 40mph, nearly hitting an oncoming car going the opposite direction. They were completely straddling the lane and if I had wavered from a straight line at all, they would have hit me or the oncoming car. Absolutely terrifying.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was walking south on Arrellaga and almost got run down by a bicyclist riding the wrong way on the sidewalk on Chapala as we intersected.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: a driver was merging onto Las Positas from Modoc using the right-turn-only lane and did not notice a bike rider in the bike lane to their right. the driver eventually noticed the rider and was able to avoid a collision, but it was a very near miss and seems like a dangerous spot.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking home after getting dinner with friends downtown and was struck at the corner of modoc and las positas by a car turning right.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was rolling  along side a moving car when she decided she was going to pull over and park. Luckily I yelled loud enough that she stopped half in the bike lane and half to the right of the bike lane. I hit the side of her car and then the right side mirror with my ribs then slid down the side of the car to the ground and was laying with my head on her car. I was yelling lots of profanities and she got out of her car and said she didn’t do it on purpose. No shit!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Middle aged woman in a pickup truck plowed into me as I proceeded along the right shoulder bike path, she was trying to turn into the shopping center. No signal, no warning. She just accelerated just ahead of me and turned right into me. I fell forward and off the bike, landing in the road. She pulled over, I yelled at her, she asked me if I was okay, if I needed an ambulance. I was bruised/bleeding, but otherwise physically unharmed so I declined.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding home from work , crossing over the overpass a young e-bike rider was coming opposite going quickly and didn’t seem to care that his e-bike was one of those large wheeled motorcycle looking vehicles that requires caution and slow down when passing others with the extra width on a more narrow area, had to swerve to far right side to possibly avoid getting swiped by him.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver at the stop sign didn’t look to their left for oncoming cyclists/pedestrians since de la vina is a one way. I had the right of way, as I had been waiting for traffic to die down at the stop sign.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I've had numerous near misses crossing over the pedestrian and bike footbridge from Modoc over to Oak Park. Cars driving west on Calle Real roll the stop sign and do not think to look to the left (where pedestrians and bikes cross the intersection from the bridge) because there are no vehicles entering the intersection from this direction. As a result, I've had scores of near misses in the evenings when returning home from work on my bike commute. Exercise caution at this intersection.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Raised edge on road…blacktop edge against raised concrete differential

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
A bicyclist walking his bike at the "crosswalk" (that is half painted at that intersection) almost got hit by a car making a right at a high speed. The bicyclist acting as a pedestrian with the right away signal, barely had time to run to avoid the collision. 
I was on my bike too but I had made a box turn in front of the cars in the middle lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on Las Positas headed south at the intersection with calle real. People are always rushing to turn right on Calle Real to get on the freeway and it's it's not clear where the safest place is for bikes  because the bike lane suddenly ends. Someone almost hit me when I was waiting at a red light and yelled at me for being in the way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car stopped at stop sign waved me on and then started to drive when I went which forced me to brake quickly and fall off my bike. The stop signs are too confusing for drivers to understand. Often drivers will also try to wave bikes on into cars turning into the neighborhood.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The wing mirror of a car that was passing me on my left struck my left elbow (we were traveling in the same direction on the same side of the road; I was in the bike lane on State Street). The car proceeded to immediately crash into the back of a parked car. It turned out the elderly driver had collapsed at the wheel, and the passenger in the car was unable to stop or steer the out-of-control vehicle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car speeding up Milpas, turned left onto Canon Perdido and into the right lane where I was stopped at the light. I had to jump off my bike and out of the way, and the car missed my by a foot. The car did not stop and sped down Canon Perdido towards State. I had a bright front light and two red tail lights on.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: DOORED while riding in the De La Vina bike lane. :-(((

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The stop signs along this bike path are dangerous. Drivers turning left into the neighborhoods are constantly trying to wave me into oncoming traffic when I have the stop on my bike.  For this reason and others cyclists always blow through the stop signs. It makes it feel safer to just ride in the street.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Large dump truck intentionally passed very close (within 2 feet).  It was intentional because the truck driver had the option not to do it.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was headed west on the new Modoc bike path, and a car, also traveling west was planning to turn left. I coasted through the intersection without checking for traffic behind me

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle did not look left before turning left resulting me having to slam brakes.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Riding across bridge, wheel entered large gap in bridge, causing my wheel become lodged which sent me flying over handlebars.  Broke 5 ribs, dislocated left shoulder, road rash.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While biking through an intersection, a car coming the other direction was turning left. They were more concerned about the cars but did not notice me, so they were speeding up toward me as I was trying to cross the intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car was turning right into the 76 gas station. They clearly didn't look because they turned immediately in front of me (I was biking next to the sidewalk in the "bike lane"). Slammed on my brakes and swerved into traffic on my left - luckily I didn't hit anything in the adjacent lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling westbound on Hollister Ave, a vehicle rolled through the stop light turning right onto Hollister Ave, causing me to swerve and slam on brakes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on a tandem bike with my son on the back on the way to Vieja Valley elementary school. We were traveling in the bike lane when a car in the traffic lane to the left of us merged into the bike lane where we were riding. I had to hit the brakes and yell to get the drivers attention. This behavior is very frequent on this stretch of road between 7:30-8:30 am when traffic backs up and cars move into the bike lane to try to go around stopped vehicles.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling westbound on Hollister through the Fairview intersection. Vehicle traveling south on Fairview making a right turn onto Hollister in the westbound direction rolled through a red light causing me to swerve and brake hard to avoid collision. I was wearing reflective vest, but maybe morning sunrise made it hard to see me. A lot of vehicles roll that turn/intersection anyways.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: There is an accident on this corner pretty much every day. Visibility is terrible from every direction and it's blind going up or down the hill. Could be better as a 4-way stop or if it had better signage for bikes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: "APS" (Alameda Padre Serra St.) on this stretch is serpentine and narrow, with poor visibility ahead especially for westbound (uphill) vehicles. I ride this stretch to work 3-5x/week, and almost every day, at least once per week, a vehicle (car, SUV, work truck) tries or does pass me with zero visibility ahead, forcing downhill vehicles to slow, stop or swerve. Forget about 3 feet to pass, cyclists are lucky to get 1'. In May one came front bumper to bumper with a downhill vehicle, no touch tho.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was riding northbound in the bike lane on de la vina when a someone quickly and suddenly opened their door into the bike lane. I was able to avoid collision but it’s just one of many close calls I have had near handlebar coffee.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car going up APS was behind me; I saw several cars coming down so I moved to the center of the uphill lane, signalling the car behind me not to pass. He tried anyway. Downhill traffic came to a full stop in order to avoid a collision (3 cars coming down).  This has happened to me several times along this stretch.

i_type: Fall
details: I needed to get from the side of the road back into the lane due to parked cars. A car sped past instead of letting me through, so I had to brake suddenly. Due to a patch of sand on the roadway, I skidded and fell. The result was a trip to the ER and a fractured arm, and minor damage to my bike. A bike lane would have prevented this accident. Most of State Street has a bike lane, why is there a gap for three blocks? This should be remedied ASAP, all it takes is a couple stripes of paint.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car pulled past me and turned right slowly into shopping center causing me to stop very suddenly.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Out of town vehicle made a right, cutting me off going straight, and I collided into their door. The women proceeded to yell at me and film me until cops came to get her away from me.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Next to tap Thai, uptown lounge, kimchi, etc. Cars are parked and they are so excited to get into the restaurant that they swing their doors open without looking. There is a bike lane but the car doors go right into the bike lane when opened. I have had at least a half dozen near misses. But it is one of the more direct routes for my commute home.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bicyclist riding in bike line was cut off by driver who quickly changed from left to right lane and then proceeded to turn right into parking lot. Rider locked up rear wheel and had to step off bike to stay upright. Car driver did not look for bike traffic and did not signal.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding with my husband, and we singled up to allow for cars to pass.  The first car moved over to the oncoming lane to pass us.  Then car directly behind the first car lane intentionally got close to us and sped up to try and overtake the first car passing.  We confronted the driver at the stop sign and she told us bike don't belong on the road and she was glad almost hit us.  White CRV, custom license plate with "SBYOUNG".

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was in the bike lane and a car whizzed by me at a very high rate of speed blaring their horn which started me  and almost caused me to lose control. It was just after sunset and getting quite dark but I had lights on and was squarely in the bike lane. Incredibly rude and dangerous driver behavior!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car backed into my bike

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A student in their mid-20s biking on Modoc towards their job (as apparently they do every morning) was hit (Modoc/Encore intersection) trying to cross to the Obern Trail from Modoc, and catapulted onto the windshield of a car, which was badly damaged/cracked.  An ambulance came, but the biker declined to be taken in, saying his helmet protected him, and that he had only suffered some scrapes and cuts. Later that day he went to the hospital and was diagnosed as having suffered a concussion.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The bike lane and the lane towards the 101 onramp dangerously intersect behind a curve in this badly planned overpass. There are no green markers for bicycles and the pavement is terrible. Some drivers are courteous enough, but many don't know how to act with bicycles crossing their lane to get to the bike lane. This is a death waiting to happen.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My friend was hit by a driver turning right into the plaza and her bike was totaled. She went to urgent care but had no lasting injuries.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The bike lane disappears, and it’s kind of a scramble against cars to establish yourself in the turn lane or straight lane. If cars turning don’t see you or don’t respect you, you have to aggressively dodge to the turn lane where there might already be a car.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car ran right through a fully red light at the pedestrian light crossing Calle Real near Ace Hardware. Thought this was the safest way to get from Calle Real to N Fairview, but this was the second car to run a red pedestrian light in this one grocery run. The light was definitely fully red for a couple seconds, and I had already started to cross. If the cars don't listen to the red light how else do I safely cross?

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a pinch point in the road at a busy intersection. The safest route is to take the lane, but this is not always possible with fast-moving traffic coming from behind. I've had completely unaware drivers squeeze me into the curb while passing.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details:
I was in a rush and there was a new curb where there didn't used to be one and it blended into the sidewalk behind it so I didn't see it.
I fractured 5 ribs, among other injuries.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car left to go up La Cumbra did not look for cyclist in lane/moving into left turn lane to get onto state. Had to decide whether to sprint and maybe get by or to slam on the brakes and take a hit. Had day running lights on and was standing tall approaching the intersection.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
E-bike rider under 16 years old riding outside his lane and dove into me and my bike in my biking lane.
Severe injury requiring emergency visit and surgery
Multiple broken bones
E bikes should not be riden by people under 16  or without proper training.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading west in the bike lane on calle real. A black bmw was waiting to turn left out of the parking lot. It accelerated right before i was going past and we both had to slam on the brakes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was using the pedestrian signal to cross Calle Real so that I could make a left out of the Trader Joe's parking lot, and a car blew right through the red light as I was starting to cross. I even waited a second, so the light was fully red for several seconds.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking northbound on Fairview, had just crossed Calle Real and was in the bike lane, and a vehicle turned right into the gas station right in front of me. I had to slam on my breaks to avoid hitting the vehicle. It's not the first time I've seen vehicles speed up to make the light at Calle Real, then slow suddenly to make the right turn into this station. Date indicated above is approximate +/- 2 months.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cars never see me when I am turning Left onto San MArcos. This intersection needs a light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was writing on La Collina, which is a school zone, on my way to Hope School, where I work. A man in a white work truck was leaning out his window yelling me to hurry up. Hurry up. I felt like the driver was harassing me and it made me feel less safe.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling northbound on La colina when a truck passed me through the school zone going too fast. They looked me dead in the eye and then rolled coal on me. I coughed and hacked for about five minutes before I could continue. It was a big gray truck with one of those support the police stickers in the back.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car failed to yield to bicycle stopped at intersection with four way stop sign. Bicyclist was a child on way to school.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle ran a red light and collided with bicycle in middle of intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was using the Turnpike entrance into Tucker's Grove to drop off my son for Wilderness Youth Project. There are two lanes on Turnpike coming from the South (the 101 was behind us, the hills in front of us); one lane is for turning left and going straight into the park, the other lane is for turning right. The light turned green and I proceeded straight through the intersection. However I slammed on my breaks to avoid hitting the cyclist on my right who was now turning left in front of me.

i_type: Fall
details: I hit a 2 inch nail in the bike lane,  which resulted in a compete blowout of my rear tire.  I was able to navigate to the side of the road right past Turnpike.  The tire was beyond repair,  While walking my bike back home with my bike in "walk mode" I accidentally hit the wrong button and my bike took off and I hit the pavement.  Just minor scrapes and bruises.  But be careful walking your e-bike in walk mode!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Was EB on Foothill and approaching the 192 NB offramp. A car rolled the stop sign and ran into me.

I fell and had road rash and property damage.  Driver stopped and got their info. Filed insurance claim.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was nearly hit from behind by a car on the Arroyo Quemada bridge, Hwy 101, along the Gaviota Coast.  Another cyclist I know has been hit and severely injured here - and is currently  suing Caltrans.
This bridge was built in 1917-18.   It's paved surface is only 21' wide with two lanes of high speed south-bound traffic and no shoulder.  It is also located on the Caltrans designated Pacific Coast Bike Route!  Caltrans needs to bypass this bridge like the nearby Arroyo Hondo bridge was.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A bicyclist was killed while crossing the slip lane.  Motorist hit bicyclist from behind.  She later died from her injuries.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: 3 of us riding down the straight part of Tepusquet toward Foxen at a good clip when someone coming up fast from behind lays on the horn very aggro. A white pickup blows by, buzzing me within inches. It pulls over in front of me and the driver leaps out shouting obscenities including "I'm gonna kill you mf-er!" and more. I don't doubt that was the intent of this large angry man who ran across the road toward me. I just escaped his reach otherwise I'd have hit the ground hard. He buzzed me again.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding straight in the bike lane with head light flashing.  A woman pulled out of the shopping center in front of me.  She didn't see me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: There is a short section of Broadway that is sharrows between bitteravia Road and Western Village Drive. I was northbound on that section and paying attention to what was ahead of me. I was in the far right lane and there were two lanes of traffic to the left of me. My Lane has sharrows on it. A truck passed me partly in my lane and cut sharply in front of me. It was a dark silver metallic Silverado pickup truck. I reported it to the police shortly afterwards.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
A white SUV (license 8ZLD031)passed me (on my bicycle) too closely (the vehicle was 12 to 18" into my lane perhaps only a foot away from me). The car was initially behind me and returned into the same lane in front of me. I was riding in the center of the sharrow lane wearing a bright yellow jacket. This was on Broadway northbound in the number 3 lane just past Betteravia Road (about in front of CVS).
Prior to the incident the car had been tailgating and honked its horn twice.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: In the bike lane on Broadway a bicyclist Road the wrong way while looking at their phone. I almost couldn't avoid them or they me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a repeat of an incident at 4:45 pm.  I reached the stop sign a white pickup pulled up behind me and honked. I checked for cross traffic and proceeded. There were cars parked along this stretch and so I took the lane. The white truck driver leaned on their horn. I felt a bit uncomfortable and harassed. at the left turn in the road, there were no cars parked so  so I moved adjacent to the curb. The truck driver continued to honk continuously. Although there was room to pass they didn't.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on the bike path headed west and stopped on the type Q quadrupole bicycle detector.  The bicycle light turned green and I started across the intersection.  I stopped quickly because a car advanced to make a right turn in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on the bike path headed west and stopped on the type Q quadrupole bicycle detector.  The bicycle light turned green and I started across the intersection.  I stopped quickly because a car advanced to make a right turn in front of me.

i_type: Fall
details: I was driving home from work at night. I came off of the battles multi-use path and turn right heading across battles Road North. I use the crosswalk line as a guide to keep me straight. It put me to the Curve in the gutter. They're the asphalt lip caused my wheel to hop and I to fall. It was the asphalt lip that was the cause of my fall.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The bike lane going south bound on college disappears for about a block just north of Battles. I was passed very aggressively by a super duty pickup truck. It seemed intentional and malicious. He revved the engine as he passed me. Although signage states bicycles may use the full lane, the driver encroached in my lane as they passed, straddling the dotted yellow center line.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Copied from Nextdoor, "I want to share with you all that my adult son was hit by a car Sunday afternoon on Broadway. He was riding in the bike lane in front of Foods Co when a car took a right into the parking lot right in front of him. Thankfully he had a motorcycle helmet on and only suffered a severe laceration to his index finger (5 stitches) when he collided with the right side rear view mirror. He works on the North end of Santa Maria and takes his E-bike up Broadway 5 days a week.   "

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding in the center of the sharrowed lane.  A pickup intentionally buzzed me.  It was within inches of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This was northbound on Broadway at the intersection with Stowell Road where the bike and car lanes must merge together into a shared travel Lane. I signaled to move left into the common Lane and a pickup truck with a trailer did not yield the right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on the bike lane and the vehicle got too close and I had to swerve closer to the sidewalk.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crossing on Stowell Rd on Miller. Car went to fast and nearly missed me and my friend.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: She was riding on the sidewalk and came to an intersection where she had the right of way and the cross street had a stop sign. i_type: Fall

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: At about 4:40pm on Friday March 15th 2024. I turned left from W Morrison Ave. onto S Broadway and headed north on my bicycle wearing my yellow jacket. About after the train tracks I noticed an extended honk coming from behind me. I continued in the center of the sharrowed #2 lane. A white truck honking its horn came up behind me and passed close to me in my lane. I felt a little shook up.  This was repeated at 5:28 pm at a different location reported separately.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: We signaled to turn left. Car behind us was patient, but the car behind them was rushing and passed them as we were merging to the suicide lane.  Angered the driver and informed them that it is a shared bike lane.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I had stopped in the center of the eastbound lane behind the limit line on Cook St. and waited to cross Broadway.  The light turned and I crossed riding in the right lane which is marked with sharrows. A driver in a black jeep passed very very close (6-12") on my left in my lane.  I yelled. He turned right on McClelland which was where I was going.  I saw he had parked at the library so I called out to him. He ignored me. He was an older man about 65. I walked over to him, he didn't respond.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

I think the sensors have stopped working.  I slowed when I entered the intersection and traffic on the far side of the avenue (heading west) stopped, so I proceeded into the intersection.  A car exiting the freeway (heading east) did NOT stop and we came *very* close to a collision.  Pretty darned close.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was nearly t-boned by a fast moving passenger vehicle traveling on Stanley Avenue in the "on ramp lane" to northbound Highway 33.  I was on the Ventura River Trail Class I bike path and was crossing Stanley. Backed-up school traffic hid a fast moving vehicle heading for the freeway.  I saw it when I was in the middle of the oncoming vehicle's lane.  I decided I had to keep moving, hit the pedals and barely made it.  Don't be lulled by pavement flashers.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver screamed at me from behind, and then revved his engine and screamed obscenities as he passed me less than 1ft away from me at high speed trying to pass before parked cars.  I was using the full lane as is a cyclist's right and gave a friendly wave when he started yelling initially.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car tried to stay in its lane while passing.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While biking in the main lane of traffic (as is your right as a cyclist) as I approached the intersection, a black car on North Oriental Street attempted to turn in left onto 10th street in front of me. She had to slow down mid turn and swerve into the oncoming lane because otherwise she would have hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Silver(?) colored 4 door car nearly ran a red light to pull a u-turn while I was riding my bike through the crosswalk with a walk sign active. The car came within less than 12" of me/my bike and the driver was visibly surprised as the car jolted to the response of it's brakes. The car had cross past the white line and into the crosswalk area.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bike rider riding east on the north sidewalk of 16th Street crossed College with the light and nearly got broad sided by a westbound car turning right (north) onto College. Rider had no lights, but was otherwise riding legally.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details:
A vehicle came inches from hitting me at high speed. This is the most dangerous spot I have found in Indianapolis.
* It’s a blind bend in the road when biking north. 
*It’s a far distance from stoplights. Cars typically drive 50mph. 
*The median is very small and not a safe spot.
* If one car happens to stop at the flashing yellow. Then the other lane typically does not. 
* needs pedestrian operated stoplight before a death occurs.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle approached from behind and began honking when they were still nearly a city block behind me. As they approached they accelerated toward me and passed within 1 foot at 40mph. They then skidded to a stop, backed up past me, and accelerated toward me a second time.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Not one but two passenger cars exited McLean, running the stop sign at speeds of 25-40 MPH, and turned north on Illinois

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car blasted through a red light eastbound on 29th at probably 45 mph.  My light had been green for a full 3 seconds.  If I had assumed it was safe when the light turned green I would have been killed.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Suburban turned into us as we were crossing in crosswalk with a green light.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding north on Sutherland Ave.  Stopped at stop sign then proceeded through.  Jeep turning left off 34th Street did not see me and hit me in the rear of the bike knocking me over.  No breaks, lots of bruises.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: The overgrowth of tree branches and undergrowth extends over the guardrail from IMA west to Knollton Rd/Cold Spring Rd/Wynnedale neighborhoods. There is also a large amount of trash and debris blocking the shoulder. This makes biking and or walking very dangerous in this area of W. 38th St.  At very least the brush needs cleared back and street cleaned. I strongly feel that a bike lane on this busy street would be safest, the shoulder of the road should be usable if maintained. Thank you.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car heading west on E. 42nd ran stop sign at Winthrop at a speed of at least 20mph.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car passed us riding 2 abreast within one foot

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A distracted motorist talking on the phone left the CVS parking lot without stopping.  The vehicle came within a foot of hitting me.  If I had not assumed the vehicle would not stop I would have been struck.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle turning left from wesftield to 56th nearly struck me while I was in the crosswalk and had the right of way.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I signaled for a left turn about a block ahead of time.  Checked my mirror and saw a van about a block behind me. As I started turn, van sped up and started to pass me. The side mirror hit my left shoulder and I went down on my left knee hip forearm and shoulder. Then the back tire hit my lower back

i_type: Fall
details:
It was dark & I did see the pothole until it was too late to avoid it. The pothole was at least 6” deep and took up almost half the lane.

My bike sustained about $450 in damage front wheel & brake.
My jacket, gloves & pants were damaged $350
Serious road rash to temple, elbow & knee.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: White Hyundai ran red light well after the light had changed.  If I would have pedaled into the intersection when I received the green light I would have been struck.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle nearly turning right from Westfield to Kessler nearly hit me while I had the right of the way in the crosswalk. Vehicle had to stop abruptly approximately 4' from me to avoid collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle attempted pass me as we were approaching a 4 way stop.  There was not enough distance for the vehicle to complete the pass before we got to the intersection.  Rather than stop beside me, the vehicle abruptly swerved to the right forcing me out of the travel lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Right-hooked while riding in the bike lane by a large truck that suddenly turned right without signaling into a shopping plaza. The car traffic at the time was moving very slow so the driver was likely trying to get around the traffic.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Cyclists were headed west bound on CR 750 N when a motorist turning left onto 750 N failed to stop at the end of the driveway for the St Malachy Catholic Church.  
Lead cyclist hit her brakes and swerved to avoid being hit by the motorist, clipping my front wheel, sending me hard to the ground.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding north on Spring Mill Road, turning left onto 79th Street.  I had a green light, used hand signals to turn left.  Midway through the turn, a pickup truck ran the light (from stopped position) to turn N on Spring Mill.  His intent seemed to be so startle me, or hit me.  I kept riding.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Motorist turning right coming out of Nora shopping center onto west bound 86th when she had a red light (No right turn on red signs posted) and Monon cyclists/pedestrians had the green crossing signal.

Did not impact my future riding because I’m already hyper aware of potential conflict zones like this and saw it coming.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Twice this summer I was crossing from the south sidewalk to the north sidewalk in the crosswalk. I had a walk sign on the opposite corner. However, southbound traffic that turns left gets a green light at the same time. I was almost hit on two occasions. I reported this to the police.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was T-boned by a car turning left across my direction of travel

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going through the roundabout when a minivan entered without looking and struck me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was headed East on Broadway Street, after stopping at the 4 way stop and letting 2 cars go (1 going north and 1 going south on 3rd Street). As I proceeded through, a distracted driver that didn't yield to anyone else in the intersection was driving South on 3rd Street. I had to swerve to miss her car.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going North on Parker Blvd and had my left hand out to indicate I was turning Left on Wahkonsa Ave, when a vehicle passed me and I was almost touching their car.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going North on Lost Lake Drive, when a car driven by a teenager that was stopped at a stop sign on Falcon Drive turned right onto Lost Lake Drive. The teenager was stopped at the stop sign on their phone before turning and didn't bother looking before turning. Contacted police and they didn't seem like they wanted to help, but asked them to talk to the kid's parents.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A white, semi was coming up from behind me.  He saw me and honked.  I was on the edge of the paved road and he was headed towards me.  I left the road to avoid being run over.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Encountered the two aggressive dogs from eight hours prior. This time they charged and lunged at my legs. Made contact with my shin resulting in a minor cut to my shin. Give there were two, and the aggressive nature, I did not make contact with the owner of the animals.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was riding a bicycle southbound in the rightmost lane of LA 315, before the intersection with LA 182.

A black pickup truck with license plate Z488576 passed close on my left while honking, splitting the two southbound travel lanes.  He then returned to the left lane where he intended to travel.
He had room to pass entirely in the left lane, without endangering me, but he did not.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a four way stop.  I was travelling South-West along Valhi.  I came to a complete stop at the stop sign.  A white SUV then came to a stop to my right.  I proceeded through the intersection.  The SUV then proceeded.  I yelled at the driver who stopped short of hitting me.  The driver then fled to Cheyenne drive where I lost visual contact.  I did not get a license plate.  Vehicle appears to be a 2014 Toyota Highlander.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was travelling East along Valhi Blvd.  A dark gray Toyota Camry with license plate 618 CDB passed within estd. 1.5-2 feet of me, squeezing between me and oncoming traffic.  I was wearing high-vis at the time of the incident.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver in Mitsubishi Outlander SUV, License plate # 5899, appears to be Louisiana "Our Environment- Our Future" plate.  Driver failed to yield to oncoming traffic at stop sign and pulled out in front of me.  I was wearing high-visibility at the time of the incident and riding in the center of the lane.  I have video of the incident.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Black Toyota Tacoma, License plate 436294, passed closer than legally required 3 feet.  I was wearing high-vis and had flashing lights.  Visibility was great.  Driver had an entire lane open and could have given me 10 feet of space if they wanted.  Instead they chose to endanger the cyclist.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding on the shoulder in the same direction as traffic.  This is a one-way street.  Another cyclist approached head-on along the same shoulder, riding against traffic, not looking in the direction of travel.  He did not see me and steered toward me until I said "hey, woah!" to get his attention.  I was wearing high-visibility at the time of the incident.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My 8 yo son was crossing Georgia (heading West on Reedie) in the crosswalk with the green light and pedestrian signal. A car driver heading south on Georgia and turning right on red onto Reedie pulled through crosswalk and stopped within inches of my son on his bike when I shouted. Driver was looking right toward where she was turning and not looking in crosswalk. She shouted from her open window, "I didn't see him!" Other cars were waiting at the light (obstructing sight lines).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Crossing the crosswalk on the trail, a vehicle slammed on breaks to yield to me crossing on the crosswalk.

I had slowed before entering the crosswalk with plenty of time for the driver to recognize me, who was ~50 yds away.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Toyota (license - 5CI9692) travelling at speed from behind passed within inches of me.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car stopped midway into the crosswalk for a pedestrian. When ped was gone, driver starting moving without noticing me approach from the other side.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: On Friday, November 3rd, 2019, a 19-year-old man was killed near 80 East College St when a dump truck struck him. The bicyclist was pronounced dead on the scene.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Motor vehicle turned left from Columbus Ave on a green ball (permitted left) without noticing I was approaching. I applied emergency braking, stopped just before entering the street as the car whizzed by 2 ft in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Return trip from school drop off. I came to a complete stop at the red light, on Cypress Street southbound. Many pedestrians waiting to cross Cypress to access Brookline High School on the northern side of Boylston St/Rt 9. Several vehicles sped towards the intersection from Boylston Street eastbound as the light changed green to yellow, and subsequently two vehicles proceeded through the intersection with the red signal, during the pedestrian phase.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was approaching the intersection of Parker and Prentiss on southbound Parker. I was preparing to turn left onto Prentiss. There was no oncoming traffic and no stop sign on Parker, so I had the right of way. A driver stopped at the stop sign on westbound Prentiss was signaling a right turn onto Parker, which not conflict with my left turn. Halfway through her right turn she decided to turn left instead, without signaling, and failed to yield. I braked hard and she passed in front of me.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Around 9 am on April 22, 2020, there was a fatal crash involving a bicyclist and a tractor-trailer truck. The bicyclist was pronounced dead at the scene.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding northwest on Longwood Ave when the vehicle next to me pulled into the bike lane to drop off a passenger without checking for traffic. This is a no parking zone.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: George Clemmer, a 71-year-old cyclist, was fatally struck by a dump truck at the corner of Massachusetts and Huntington avenues.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Friday, February 15th, 2019, a 69-year-old Cambridge woman was struck and killed by a cement truck while riding her bike. Emergency crews responded to a 1:30 p.m. report of a pedestrian crash in the area of Brookline Avenue at Park Drive. The cyclist was later pronounced dead at Brigham and Women’s Hospital.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was turning left from Dartmouth northbound to Blagden westbound and was in the inner left turn lane (there are two left turn lanes here, which then feed into, from right to left, Blagden, Huntington and the Masspike). A minivan passed me on the right and then crossed directly in front of me to get into the outer left turn lane and on to the Masspike. I had to brake to avoid a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding westbound on St James Ave preparing to turn right onto Dartmouth and the vehicle in front of me stopped to pick up a passenger, blocking traffic. I went around the vehicle, but the driver started to drive again just as I was turning right in front of him.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A trucker turned right onto Beacon Street from Massachusetts Avenue into the path of a 38-year-old cyclist who was crushed by the trailer’s rear wheels. The cyclist was rushed to the hospital, where they were later pronounced dead.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was turning left from EB Essex onto NB Atlantic. There are three left turn lanes here, and I was in the rightmost one, which is also a bus lane (there is no bike lane on Essex). I had made my turn and entered the right-side bike lane on Atlantic. A vehicle that had been in the center lane crossed the bike lane to get to a right turn lane to the right of the bike lane; I had to brake hard to allow them to pass in front of me rather than hitting me from the side.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: At approximately 3:20 a.m. Sunday morning, May 1st, 2017, a driver of a silver 4-door sedan hit and dragged a man riding his bike on Commonwealth Avenue and Claredon Street. The cyclist, a 29-year-old man, was taken to the hospital with life-threatening injuries. The cyclist died later at the hospital.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cars at this intersection use bike lane as an additional merge lane onto bridge, I am often side swiped by cars here. This particular incident knocked me off my bike. The car fled away. Hit and run.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding northeastbound on Atlantic Ave in the right-side bike lane. There is no street parking here. A taxi was stopped in traffic at the red light. The passenger opened her door into the bike lane and narrowly missed me. I was not watching for/expecting to be doored here since there is no street parking.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: In front of Massachusetts State House, only one lane here for a block so I took the lane. Livery driver attempted to pass me anyhow, despite oncoming traffic - was only able to avoid collision because I saw them in my peripheral vision and swerved at the last second.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was in the bike lane on Cambridge St NB, and a pickup truck merged across the bike lane to access the parking lane. I had to brake hard to avoid a collision.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Side swiped by a car turning right, did not look before turning into bike lane. I put my hand out to brace against car and sprained my hand.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking straight through an intersection in a marked bikelane and the vehicle turned right through the lane without checking for oncoming traffic. I couldn't stop in time and rear-ended them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding northbound on the Washington Street bridge. An auto-hauler semi passed me in the left lane, but the left lane was closed for construction ahead. As I gained speed coming down from the center of the bridge, the driver merged back into my lane, forcing me to brake to avoid a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding northwest on Hampshire St, texting driver passed me with only inches to spare.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling westbound in bike lane when northbound driver on Cardinal Medeiros turn eastbound onto Cambridge and quickly turned left trying to go onto Warren St. I swerved and slapped the hood of the car before the driver drove off.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling eastbound on Cambridge St in bike lane, traffic backed up from the light. Driver wanting to turn right pulled into bike lane to go around stopped traffic right in front of me without checking. I braked hard and still almost collided - if I hadn't just replaced my brake pads, likely would have been a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding southwest in the bike lane on my bike (and towing a trailer) Alford Street when a white SUV passed me and immediately made a hard right turn in front of me. I had to brake to avoid a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Gray minivan with driver on cell phone passed me in my lane rather than using adjacent lane (two southbound lanes here), passed within ~6 inches of my handlebars traveling probably 10-15 mph faster than I was. No chance for me to avoid as I could not hear the vehicle approaching due to wind on the bridge, and there was a guardrail to my right.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This intersection features an un-raised and poorly marked crosswalk on a highway off ramp which is heavily used by people on bikes and on foot connecting to 3 mixed use paths and a rapid transit station. Drivers frequently come down the off ramp far too quickly and fail to yield to bikes and pedals in the crosswalk. I am nearly hit by a car on my bike at least twice a week and I see the same happen to many others.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle turning right from Acorn Park Dr onto the access road stopped at the stop sign, so I entered the crosswalk on my bike, the driver evidently did not look right or forward, only left (towards oncoming car traffic), and accelerated into me. Fortunate he stopped quickly but not before knocking me from my bike and crushing the front wheel. Driver stopped, no police called.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cyclist in Crosswalk crossing two lanes first lane of cars were stopped second lane car did not stop

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Aggressive pass to "prove a point"

i_type: Fall
details: Foot path instead of sidewalk. Didn't see the lack of curb cutout.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

The speed limit on this road is 35.   There is a 3rd drive/parking lane on this road with plenty of room for cyclists.  It's an

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Trash bins are routinely placed in the bicycle lane on Beakes, causing the cyclist to either stop suddenly or swerve into traffic.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was moving east on plymouth rd on the north side of the road. The car was exiting  willow tree apartments. I believe they were turning right since they were only looking left to see when there is a gap in traffic and didn't see me  on the path/driveway to their right. They passed the stop sign before the path and stopped right before the turn. When I saw them coming I hit the brakes and skidded. I was able to stop and they stopped an inch away from. They still hadn't seen me at this point

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Coming off the Gateway Trail at Brady Street, motor vehicles don't heed the stop sign....often rolling through or stopping well after the sign and the trail end intersection.  Always double check.   Young female driver was on her phone.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding as close to the right as possible on the asphalt.  White, regular cab Chevy Pickup (2002 Vintage) drives past me within a foot to me on a 2 lane road.  There was no opposing traffic at the time vehicle past.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Travelling in the protected bike lane westbound along Plymouth Ave. Had just passed through the intersection, and a left turning car pulled directly in front of me, causing me to collide with it's passenger side. The car was turning left across a lane of traffic into the parking lot of the liquor store, so I unquestioningly had the right of way. 

I and my bike, were fortunately uninjured. Some lovely northsiders checked on me, and told me of their own story of being hit by a car there too.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: We were about to enter a lighted pedestrian corridor with lights flashing. Vehicles had stopped in some lanes and a child on a bike was in the roadway. A vehicle dis not slow as it approached the corridor and had to slam on its brakes to avoid hitting the child.
