I was not going too fast but the bike flipped and I fell my face down. I chipped my tooth and ended up getting a root canal. I had several superficial and deep cuts as well

i_type: Fall
details: Wheel caught in trolley track as I was turning left over them. I fell to the left, injuring both wrists, leg, rib and nose. There were no warning signs about track danger from the place I entered Delmar to the place I turned.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was bicycling straight through this intersection on green light at night with a bike like in the front and rear. An oncoming truck turned left out of the straight lane, did not see me, and hit me with the right front of the truck as the vehicle was turning left. I was tossed in the air from the impact. The driver stayed, along with multiple witnesses as police and ambulance came. The driver was at fault and insurance covered damages to my bike (bent frame and handlebars).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing the intersection headed North on Van Buren St. (from the south side) in the bike lane, so going straight. In succession, 2 vehicles headed west on broadway ran the red light- the first turning right on red (across the bike lane) without stopping, the second driving straight through the red light at full speed, causing multiple cars crossing North/South and me on my bike (I was thankfully still in the south portion of the intersection) to slam brakes and lay on horns.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: crossing broadway north to south on van buren st. (west side crosswalk). car headed east on broadway pulled through right-hand turn lane without stopping for crosswalk (cars stopped in other two eastbound lanes, so that car wouldn't have been able to see me, but didn't stop none-the-less). I know enough about this intersection at this point to look for that potential and slammed my brakes and turned left so as to not be hit by them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crossing E. Broadway from south to north on the West side of the intersection. I was on the cross walk because I biking home from picking my kid up from childcare (she was in a trailer).  I had a walk sign and crossed the lanes of east-bound (stopped) traffic, but was stranded waiting in the middle of the crosswalk for the southbound cars turning right on red to stop to let me cross. None stopped before the walk signal ended and I was stranded waving to let me finish crossing. Unnerving.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing the intersection on a green light and someone ran a red light and nearly hit me plus two other cars

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While biking into town on Broadway from E. Msla I was crossing Van Buren on green/walk sign.  The bike lane ends at this intersection so I was attempting to bike across Van Buren and onto the Rux trail.  A vehicle turning right started to proceed through the intersection, nearly causing an accident, stopped, blocking access to the bike trail so I had to stop in the intersection/crosswalk, and yell/signal for them to proceed so I could access the bike trail.  This is not the 1st time.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was biking kids to soccer practice along trail. Driver of right turning car leaving hospital driveway was only looking left for gap in traffic. She started to pull out without looking for trail traffic at all, so I shouted "are you paying attention? No, you're not" on approach. She gunned it instead of stopping. I had to slam on my brakes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: An old lady in a midsize hatchback passed me while I was riding in the west bound bike lane.  After being in front of me for about 2 or 3 seconds, she immediately turned right directly in front of me.  Even though she had just passed me seconds prior, she seemed completely unaware that I was immediately behind and to the right of her.  I was paying close attention and slammed on my bike brakes and stopped before I ran into her car.  She didn't notice me even as she turned.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crossing south ave south bound on park.  When approaching stop sign we moved to center of travel lane for crossing.  Aggravated driver sped up behind us and yelled to get out of the road, saying “your not a car”. I told him  it’s my travel lane.  His vehicle proximity to my child and road rage behavior was traumatizing to myself and my child. He was also taking his kid to school.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My son was riding his bike to school (CS Porter) on the sidewalk. a vehicle was stopped at the intersection so my son though they saw him. When he rode into the intersection, the car moved to enter traffic and they collided. My son fell from his bike and the car drove away. My son was not hurt but was very scared. The car behind the vehicle stopped and rendered aid but didn't leave their contact information. No report was filed due to lack of information.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking north on 27th and was in the intersection with Sunset Ln. Driver on Sunset making a right onto 27th did a quick look down 27th but didn't notice me in the intersection and was accelerating to make the turn while still looking south. I swerved into the other lane and the driver happened to look up in time to slam the brakes and stop in the road. Waved an apology and then passed me cautiously further down 27th.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car passed me while there was also oncoming traffic so they passed quite close. This would've been fine but there was also a parked car ahead so I had to brake quickly and stop so I wouldn't hit the passing car or parked car.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on my e-scooter headed W on 5th street on a green light in the  bike lane. A truck ran a red light and (luckily) I smacked into his driver side door. If it was .5 seconds sooner I would have been smashed by him and probably paralyzed or worse. I was the only person going through the intersection at the time, and all cars facing north/south (except the truck that ran the red) were all at the stoplight and witnessed the crash.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: A car door opened into the southbound bikelane right before I rode up. I braked hard and the driver thankfully noticed last minute and pulled their door in slightly so I could pass without veering too much into the traffic lane or hitting them.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was in the bike lane approaching the intersection of Orange and Front, daughter in the bright green bike trailer, preparing to turn right. I signaled with my left arm and a copper colored compact car encroached on my path. Before I knew it, my left elbow collided with their right rear window. The vehicle took off after a very quick stop, not sure if they realized they'd just about run us over.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver ran the red light on broadway as I was riding through the intersection on Ryman with a green light. I was struck from the left and was ejected from my bike. I was transported to the hospital via ambulance.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing Broadway to the north in the bike-lane, with a green light and a car heading south, turned left, eastward, into me. She sped up as I hit my brakes and turned behind her, sliding along her rear fender.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was turning east onto West Pine Street from Woody Street. I signaled, but as I turned a minivan began backing out of an angled parking spot in front of the county building. The rear-left corner of the minivan hit my right shoulder, ripping my hand from the handle bars. The bike wobbled and spun halfway around, but I was able to keep my balance. The man stopped reversing and made a scared face. I looked back, also shook up, but waved to indicate that I believed I was not hurt.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was eastbound in the painted bike lane on Spruce.  A car traveling in the same direction wanted to turn left on Higgins, and stopped to wait for oncoming traffic. The pickup truck behind that car veered into my bike lane in order to illegally pass the car and proceed straight. In order to avoid being struck I had to brake suddenly, almost spilling. The truck driver sailed on, either oblivious or uncaring. I thought bike lane paint would stop dangerous drivers. Was I wrong?

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: crossing Broadway from S to N at Van Buren on crosswalk/bike path on W side of intersection with walk-light. Southbound driver on Van Buren (large pick up truck) turned right without looking (I had right of way in crosswalk, with lights on & my kid in the bike trailer). I braked hard/stopped waved my arms and yelled. Driver stopped and driver behind him nearly read-ended him, honked and pulled around him and then also nearly hit me. In the end I backed up my bike and they both continued.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crossing Broadway from North to South on bike path (on W side) that parallels Van Buren St.   Cars turning right on red (during advanced walk signal) and then right on green (still during walk signal) from Van Buren onto Broadway didn't yield to pedestrians (me), despite my having stepped off the curb, waving, having blinking lights front & back.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was pulling my child in a bike trailer headed southbound on Van Buren. I was waiting on the sidewalk on the northwest corner of the intersection for the "walk" light to turn to "walk". Once it turned green, I started crossing the intersection and a car in the southbound right turn lane (the one closest to me) started turning right and I had to shout and wave at the driver to get their attention to get them to stop turning. They would have hit me and my child if they had not stopped.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: going through intersection on green light to access Rux trail, vehicle headed south on Van Buren was turning right onto E Broadway nearly hit me.  I had to brake quickly, they had to brake quickly to avoid a collision.  They were turning right on red.  This happens regularly at this intersection with motorists turning right on red this is just the most recent occasoion.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Large van passed me going east on E Broadway then turned right into the Pizza Hut parking lot directly in front of me.  I had to slam on brakes and very quickly come to a complete stop.  Any closer and I would have hit them or had to hit the ground to avoid hitting them.  Extremely scary incident.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking northbound with my kid in a bike trailer on the bike/ped path along the side of the road and crossing the eastbound interstate on ramp when a vehicle coming north on Van Buren (and turning east onto the interstate) sped into sight underneath the railroad underpass and came uncomfortably close to hitting myself and my child. There is HORRIBLE visibility for pedestrians crossing at this intersection, it is very dangerous.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car waiting for pedestrian going northbound didn't acknowledge right-of-way for bicyclist on Pine

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was southbound on Greenough, crossed the tracks, and continued in the painted bike lane west on Spruce. A car was stopped on Spruce looking to turn left onto Madison. A pickup truck driver did not want to wait for the car to turn, so veered around the car to the right and drove in the painted bike lane, missing me by about three feet, and only because I was riding defensively instead of simply owning the bike lane.  The idea that painted bike lanes protect bicyclists is ludicrous.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cars eastbound on Pine, turning left on Pattee, didn't acknowledge right-of-way for bicyclist on Pine

i_type: Fall
details: Test

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Eastbound traffic on Spruce Street had a green light, but a left-turning car was waiting to turn and perforce a line of 6 or so cars was waiting behind it. The bicyclist traveling the same direction in front of me passed these vehicles in the bike lane at roughly 10 mph. When the front car turned left and the line of cars began moving, the second car behind it turned right, across the bike lane, without regard for the bicyclist, forcing the bicyclist to slam on his brakes and skid to a stop.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was westbound on Spruce in the bike lane. The light at Higgins was red, and I stopped. A car traveling in the same direction pulled to a stop next to me. When the light turned green the driver accelerated and turned right onto Higgins forcing me to stop or be crushed.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading west on Spruce St in the bike lane. A car in the angled parking on my side of the street either did not see me or did not care, and backed out. I swerved into the traffic lane and the driver's vehicle missed me by about a foot.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Stopped at a red light in a bike lane, a right turning truck to my left turned right on red through my lane, hitting my bike and my elbow with his mirror and rear end of his pickup. Not sure if he even knew he hit someone - I yelled but he did not stop.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver intentionally passed too close (a couple inches, close enough that pedestrians nearby screamed) and yelled at me to get out of the way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle in the oncoming direction turned left into a parking lot in my path of travel. If I had not slammed on my brakes and yelled I would have been hit. This crash will not impact my cycling, as I am a "strong and fearless" rider who uses this route daily to and from work.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A van driver passed me while laying on his horn and swerving to the right, trying to force me into parked cars.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was headed east on Palmer street crossing broadway waiting at the red light.  The light turned green and I proceeded straight, and a car headed west on Palmer turning left/south onto Broadway started turning left and almost hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was westbound on Spruce, in the painted bike lane. The bike lane is sandwiched between parallel parked cars and vehicle traffic. A driver stepped into the bike lane from the front of their car without looking left into the bike lane causing me to swerve into traffic and barely avoid the pedestrian.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: headed SW on Van Buren Street in bike lane. Fed Ex truck ahead of me pulled over and parked in bike lane (there is no on-street parking on this block), causing me to veer into traffic lane, coincidentally at the same time that an oncoming/NE-bound vehicle crossed into the SW-bound lane to give a wide berth to a cyclist in the bike lane on the NE-bound side of the street. Lots of swerving of bikes (my own and the other cyclist) and cars (the NE-bound vehicle) ensued.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was southbound on Duncan. When the crappy painted bike lane disappeared I moved to the center of the lane as the sharrows indicate. A southbound pickup truck driver elected to pass me by straddling the double yellow lane divider. As we came around the blind corner a northbound car was revealed and the truck veered sharply back into the southbound lane, forcing me to brake and veer hard to the edge of the road.  Failed infrastructure and bad driving endangered my life. Again.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: He was following me

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Bicycle crossing intersection. Vehicle making a right turn and did not look before making the turn.  Bicyclist thought they had made eye contact with driver but apparently did not.  Bicycle struck by from of vehicle.  Major road rash but no treatment sought.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling eb on 9th St and had just crossed Sierra after that light turned green. Green light signal came on for us traveling eb about 100 yards before I reached Virginia, so just kept pedaling east. Car traveling nb on Virginia blatantly ran red light and I had to swerve/brake to avoid being hit from the side. Driver continued through intersection at full speed and left scene

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details:
I was driving my car ~25 mph in a 25 zone in Incline Village NV. I stopped quickly to make a right turn.  An E-Scooter, that was overtaking me, failed to stop and hit me. The E-Scooter was doing 35 mph, downhill, trying to pass on the right shoulder. He hit my front fender and rode another 50 feet before stopping.  After confirming that he was not injured, he said go back to California.
Keith Curtiss, Santa Barbara CA
The "What type of bicycle were you riding?" should be What type of vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was traveling eb on 9th St and had just crossed Sierra after that light turned green. Green light signal came on for us traveling eb about 100 yards before I reached Virginia, so just kept pedaling east. Car traveling nb on Virginia blatantly ran red light and I had to swerve/brake to avoid being hit from the side. Driver continued through intersection at full speed and left scene

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Motorist purposely brushed by me. My Fly6 rear tail light camera shows the license plate: Nevada: LV ED49

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling north along 8th street, a vehicle failed to yield at the stop sign at 8th St & Court St. The vehicle ran the stop sign at full speed, resulting in a near miss.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Coming down Janes Chapel Road, there was a car parked on the side of the road in the opposing lane, and an approaching car went around the parked car, coming into my lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The road has not bike line or no painted lines. And people don't seem to care for bikers to share the road. I would say it's not safe to ride your bike there at all.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Making left turn onto minor arterial was surprised by oncoming car moving very fast.  Stranded in Two way left turn lane (TWLTL) while rush hour traffic went by both directions.  Suddenly felt threat and looked up to see oncoming truck using center lane TWLTL as acceleration lane

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle tried to make a left turn from the opposite side of the intersection, and almost hit me as I rode through the intersection.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding on the sidewalk on the wrong side and this very nice old lady was stopped turning right at a gas station. I slowed down and thought she was stopped for long enough for me to go. She didn’t see me and slowly edged into my bike and bent the rim of the front tire. I slowly fell or descended from my bike and just ended up with a bruise.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I got off the bike trail on Alameda and was riding to the baca rail yard. An elderly man ran the stop sign and hit me on my bike

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A truck was speeding down the road in the wrong lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Person turning left at a light when I had the signal, they had a green if clear signal, almost hit me. We were going the same direction initially. It was rush hour.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: It was dark. I was turning into a driveway and the guy was trying to pass me. He was too close. When I went to turn, I almost ran into him because I turned a little. Probably my fault, but I feel like he was too close. I was trying to ride in the middle of the street so that no one would pass.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I would normally never ride on this road, it is inhospitable to anything but cars, but I accidentally placed my Chipotle order at the wrong store. Right right-turning driver (Wendover onto Providence) nearly hit me while I was crossing Wendover, heading south on Providence. (I was using the crosswalk and had been cycling on the sidewalk)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver stopped in the middle of the road with their right indicator on. Seemed to be treating the intersection as a 4-way stop and caused confusion for all. I passed them on their left and was nearly hit by the driver behind me also executing a pass. not to mention the drivers on the cross street inching into the roadway to take advantage of this driver's misunderstanding.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver turning right into my lane side-swiped me while I was clearing the intersection. Gave them a good couple of kicks and confronted the driver. He was calm and apologetic but also insisted that I belonged on the sidewalk. Admitted that he did not see me because he had been on his phone navigating. At which point I should have pointed out that he still would not have seen me had I been in the crosswalk, as he so desired. His wife was visibly uncomfortable by the whole interaction.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver ran a long stale red light as myself and other drivers were entering the intersection on our green light. This is far to common in this and other sun-belt cities. We need to bring back traffic enforcement.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: nearly hit by vehicle turning left onto Kenilworth from Romany. I did not have a front light at the time and have ridden with running day lights ever since.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turning left from Baldwin onto Kings paused in their turn as they saw me approaching the crosswalk from the creek bridge. They had plenty of time to complete their turn so I slowed to let the go, but they were not budging. By the time I arrived at the crosswalk, I felt obligated to proceed but did so without activating the RRFB. As I entered the crosswalk a jeep came barrelling around the bend in the adjacent lane. Without my pedal lights, I doubt this other driver would have seen me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver did not yield to HAWK signal during rush hour, I'm stubborn and continued into the intersection because I saw them see the signal. They had to slam on their breaks and proceeded to yell at me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Drive of heavily tinted dodge charger blew through RRFB at a high rate of speed without any indication of slowing while I was more than halfway through the crosswalk, walking my bike. They passed in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: After activating the HAWK signal and proceeding into the crosswalk a driver turning left from Dunevant St onto S Tryon St used the break in traffic to execute their turn. They did not see me until they arrived at the crosswalk and I was directly in their path. I think a fully signalized intersection may be necessary with all this apartment buildings coming online in the next few months. It is nearly impossible for cars to take a left here, but there is demand for that possibility

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was behind a vehicle that signaled and began making a right turn at the residential intersection. They were moving a little slow for my current pace so I moved to the left of the center after checking that there was no oncoming traffic. The driver changed their mind as I was coming up beside them and took a left into the church parking lot. Very near to a collision, but we were both moving quite slowly, I was able to turn away from them and they were very apologetic. We were both at fault.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: confusion over four-way-stop ROW, we both proceeded and continued into the intersection. No collision and no need to turn, we were both moving slowly enough to navigate the intersection together

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: arrived at a four-way stop well after a vehicle to my right. Waited for them to proceed, but nothing for 3-4 seconds. I assumed the driver was on their phone, but could not be certain because of their blacked-out windows. I chose to move into the intersection after the driver forfeited their right of way due to inaction. Of course, as I started moving they lurched into the intersection and had to make a hard break to avoid t-boning me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Elderly driver coming at me across the road center-line and driving into the sun's glare. She swerved to the right a bit too late for comfort. I wish we lived in a world where elderly people were empowered to hang up their car keys and enjoy a safe pedestrian life.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver behind me was trying to give me space to merge into travel lane past the line of parked cars in front of us, I was opting to stop behind parked cars and wait for this wave of traffic to clear. While their actions were generous, it confused and frustrated the drivers behind them.  Someone could easily have rear-ended that driver pushing them into me and pinning me to the parked car I was waiting behind. I'll continue to avoid this route, only went this way because the river path is blocked

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Rider was in crosswalk heading contraflow on Providence towards uptown. A driver of a large SUV cut off the rider while making a right turn onto Queens from Providence.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was tailgated by a driver aggressively honking at me. This road is marked as a sharrow bike route between Plaza Midwood and the hospital; it is two lanes with no shoulder and curb-tight sidewalks. In order to ride safely around the curve, one must take the lane. It has been a while since I took this route and now I am reminded why.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: garbage truck turning left onto Hawkins turned in front of me and cut me off. There were no sight obstructions, I watched the driver not appropriately check if they had a clear entry onto the roadway.  gross negligence.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Impatient driver turning left from West Blvd onto South Blvd took a hasty left at the green light to beat oncoming traffic, He did not account for the pedestrians who had a leading walk sign. Cut off myself and several other walkers at a high rate of speed and acceleration. Incredibly selfish behavior; too bad we don't live in a society that would appropriately penalize such antisocial and reckless actions.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of a lifted Tacoma with tinted windows executing an aggressive left turn into the TJ's parking lot. They cut me off while I, with the right of way, was making a right turn into the parking lot. This is the closest I've come to whacking a vehicle with the u-lock in my back pocket, but chose to practice restraint.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: the driver of a large tree-trimming truck stopped on a red blocking the entire crosswalk. This is a no-turn-on red intersection. The truck was so large a cyclist had to go around the front rather than behind. The hood height of the truck prevented the driver from seeing the cyclist and the cyclist was pushed dangerously close to high speed rush hour traffic. Luckily the truck driver did not try to turn while the cyclist was in front of them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: classic case of a crosswalk across a multi-lane road. Driver nearest stops to let me proceed while drivers in the far lane plow ahead. Man in large pickup truck had to slam on his breaks to keep from hitting me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver found themselves stopped in the middle of the intersection because the light rail train was passing. I proceeded around their rear and they started to back-up as I was passing. I don't think I made the right decision, I also think drivers should be more careful about entering intersections before they know if they can clear them. A little common sense and engagement in the act of driving goes a long way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: while walking my bike across a HAWK crosswalk, a driver in the far lane ignored the flashing lights and continued through the intersection going at least 45mph.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver going way too fast for this road segment (~45) passed by way too close. When I caught up to them at the light, they were blasting music and taking selfies, love a distracted driver. Good reminder of why I avoid these bike lanes on Hawthorne. They are nice and wide, but without a curb or bollard protection I will never feel save riding on this street. Far too many drivers, use the bike lane to avoid driving on the trolley tracks.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver of an emotional support monster truck with black tinted windows cut off my right of way to execute their left turn before I could clear the intersection (I was headed straight through).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passed on right (in metered parking ROW) at a high rate of speed (easily over 45mph) and nearly hit a parked car before merging back in front of me. Reeked of marijuana

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading strait along Clement Avenue to the neighborhood side, from the park side. A vehicle arrived at the other side of the non-signalized intersection well after myself. They stopped. While waiting for traffic to clear a vehicle on 7th heading NW began a turn onto my side of Clement. After this driver cleared my path I was clear to enter and cross the intersection. Driver across road also entered to begin an unsignaled left turn. The turning vehicle blocked both our sight line of eachoth

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: the vehicle nearly hit me while I was walking my bike across HAWK crosswalk. They obviously saw me and had plenty of time to slow down; attempted to swerve around me by cutting into the middle turn lane, but could not find room between me and the vehicles stopped in the other side of the signal (their oncoming traffic). They were yelling and cursing.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: After arriving at the intersection with 7th St, I moved slightly to the right to activate the RRFB so I could use the crosswalk, since there was heavy morning traffic. A driver of a large suburban was behind me and decided to make their right turn onto 7th as I was entering the crosswalk. I've noticed a pernicious pattern of drivers usurping a pedestrians right of way at signalized crosswalks, when they are turning onto a larger arterial.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Encountered a driver coming towards me at a relatively high speed (~30mph on a road that should be traversed between 15 and 20mph). They were on the wrong side of the road and driving into the morning sunrise and swerved back to their side a bit too late for comfort.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: negligent and disengaged driver at a four-way stop. They clearly had the right of way, as I had arrived at the intersection well after them. I stopped to wait for them to clear the intersection. They did not move, nor did they wave me through, they just sat there, So I proceeded to enter and as I moved in front of their vehicle they decide that was the best time to reengage with their driving trip. We need to enact rigorous remedial courses for incompetent drivers.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: arrived at a four-way stop about 2-3 seconds after a jeep, the jeep was at a full stop and I slowed to observe which direction they were headed. Given no turn signals were on I assumed they were headed straight and proceeded with a quasi "Idaho Stop" by continuing into the intersection at a slow clip (< 3mph).  After entering the intersection, the driver decided they were going to turn left and cut me off to do so while giving me the bird.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver arrived at the four-way stop well before me (~7 seconds), they could have cleared the intersection before my arrival. When I got to the stop they were still stationary and showing no signs of moving so I proceeded straight through. Of course, as I enter the intersection they lurch to a start and then break hard after seeing me. I assume this is a case of a driver using an intersection as a space to double-check their navigation. I see this behavior quite frequently.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While making my way through the intersection a driver to my right arrived at their stop sign and proceed to blow through it with little reduction in speed. They were feet from broadsiding me, before screeching to a halt. No question I had the right of way and they were at fault. I decided not to confront this driver because she looked immediately stunned and guilty, but this is easily the closest I've come to serious injury in Charlotte.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turned left directly in front of me. had to really gas it to keep from hitting me. Unfortunately, my pedal lights were out, but I did have a front light and a reflective jacket on.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing Hawthorne from the south to north on the left side of the road using the signalized crosswalk to enter the main part of Independence park. A vehicle turning right from 7th onto Hawthorne was looking left and nearly turned into me. I was fully expecting them to hit me, but somehow stopped in time. This was during morning rush hour, I am now more hesitant about riding when drivers are more stressed and distracted.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver of a minivan took extra liberties with the leading left signal from 7th onto Hawthorn. Well after their arrow had turner red and I had entered the crosswalk on the walking person, they cut in front of me to execute their left turn. I'm cautious and am always looking over my shoulder at intersections, but it is this kind of behavior that kills people. I prefer lagging left turn signals for pedestrian safety.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: large truck driven by teenager behind me, both of us turning left onto Pecan from Bay Street.  At the railroad tracks truck proceeded in to oncoming traffic to pass. Had to sharply merge back into my lane of travel to avoid hitting oncoming traffic. This is a common issue on this stretch of road.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car crossed a double yellow lane to try pass me on a curve then swerved back into the lane to avoid collision with another car. Frequently see cars bypass the double yellow line at this curve.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was very nearly hit by the driver of a BMW sedan going way too fast on Caldwell St. I was midway through the intersection when they neglected to stop or yield to my right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Some car-brained, luxury sports car driver, thought it was perfectly acceptable to execute a three point turn in the middle of the intersection. They nearly backed into me because I assumed they were making a left turn so I proceed behind them to head straight through the intersection. Main character syndrome on full, unadulterated, display.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Antagonized by driver of muscle car while turning onto road out of gym parking lot. Driver sped up and hard-breaked behind me on a traffic clogged road, while revving engine.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver parked their emotional support truck at the four way stop in the Y parking lot. I had to go around them into oncoming traffic and was nearly hit by a left turning vehicle because we could not see each other around or through the lifted / tinted truck. The driver also decided to get under way as I was passing in front of them, I'm surprised they saw me and braked since my head just barely breached the top of their hood.

i_type: Fall
details: turning right onto Elizabeth into the left-hand turn-lane at the intersection with Kind Drive. underestimated the angle of attack across the light rail tracks and wheels fell into the grooves, bucking me off. Thankfully, no cars around at the time.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: antagonized by the driver behind me. Pretty classic situation of someone getting irritated and laying on the horn while I'm keeping pace with the surrounding traffic.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: nearly rear ended while stopped in left lane waiting to make a left turn onto Bland towards the rail trail. This was a risky maneuver to begin with, will not be executing again.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: There were a group of hospital workers heading into the Charlottetowne Ave tunnel as I was exiting and taking a right around the stadium. I hugged the right side of the path, but still came close enough for one of them to flinch in surprise. Since then I try to keep things slow out of the tunnel and ring my bell multiple times. A mirror would be useful for this blind turn.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: close pass, NC license plate: HCV-2951, Nissan Sentra

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: ban right on red. driver hardly slowed while rounding the corner from south onto carson while I was making my way straight through the intersection. Their view was blocked by a large truck stopped in their adjacent lane at the light. Truly reckless to drive so fast at an intersection with an obstructed. view, could easily have maimed a pedestrian in the crosswalk. They had to slam on their breaks not to hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: nearly collided with pedestrian while turning the corner around the stadium, this area could really use some mirrors... this corner and the underpass corner specifically. I fully support a pedestrian's right to not be fully alert, but this does mean that my bell ringing around corners does not always cut it. As usual, I took this turn very slowly so a collision was averted, but this is a prime location for an injury-inducing collision with an e-bike or e-scooter rider.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver of mustang attempted to execute a right turn on red while I was crossing in front of them. They had to slam on their brakes not to bowl me over. Love to see that an ambulance driver executed that same illegal maneuver before I arrived at the intersection. Drivers in this town do whatever they care to do with impunity.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: multiple drivers turning right on red, cutting off pedestrians on the x-Charlotte trail, including a uniformed officer (police or sheriff) in her personal truck. I had to ride directly in front of her to keep her from going and to stop this parade of oblivious drivers.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver in a large truck performing illegal right on red onto Kings from Elizabeth nearly hit me while I was crossing the street on the CLT path.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver illegally turning right onto Kings from Elizabeth on a red. Blocking my crossing path and facing left to find an opening in traffic. The driver nearly executed a right turn while I was directly in front of their hood, thankfully their passenger alerted them to my presence.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: another driver about to execute an illegal right on red while I am passing in front of them. I'm going to get quite the payout one of these days.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: right-turning driver fully blocking the crosswalk, had to knock on their hood to make sure they noticed me. Then a left-turning driveer failed to yield as I made my way through the crosswalk. If Charlotte wants the x-charlotte trail to be a safe riding path for the masses, this intersection needs to change. (The left-turning truck had fully blacked-out windows, I don't know if they saw me or not)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turning left into the parking lot cut in front of me. I would have hit them, had I not swerved to the left. I recognize that people parking here almost never have to deal with oncoming traffic, driving is too easy, we need to make it so that people are more engaged and not on autopilot. Also, they were driving into the glare of the morning sun.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: while making a left from Commonwealth onto Pecan a driver of a lifted jeep, headed south, blew through their stop sign without any reduction in speed and nearly side swiped me. Had I been further along in my turn execution they would have plowed me down. (I confronted the driver and they claimed to not have seen me. I suspect they were on their phone).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: cut off by impatient bmw

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: ban right on red. Driver hardly slowed as they came speeding through the crosswalk I was using while they had a red light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of a large ford pickup truck blew through stale red light, somewhere between 5 and 10 seconds after their light had turned red and other cars in their adjacent travel lanes had come to a full stop. There was no indication that they breaked or attempted to slow. I was more than halfway through the intersection when the crossed the intersection behind me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver in a large truck cut off a man and his two children on their cargo bike. Biker was in front of me heading north on the plaza bike lane and the driver made a hasty left onto Hamorton Place when there was a gap in rush hour vehicular traffic. This is the same intersection where a woman was killed on her bike earlier this year.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: weaving among a line of left turning vehicles that would not yield to my right of way. I'm stubborn and this was a bit reckless. When looking over my right shoulder to check clearance for oncoming vehicle, I notice the man was fully engaged in using his phone while executing a left turn. Ban drivers.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turned left while myself and another rider had the right of why on the bike path crossing. They turned left in front of me and I clipped the rear of driver side of vehicle. The driver did stop to check that I was okay and in an effort for full transparency, this was partially my fault. I stubbornly assumed my right of way even though I saw the driver had begun their turn just as I was entering the crossing.  I did misjudge how quickly they would complete their turn.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver crossing 6th Street did not check to see if the cyclelink was clear of riders (me) before executing their crossing. They came within inches of hitting me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: close right-hook

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turning onto 8th from McDowell nearly hit me as I was heading straight on the Uptown CycleLink protected bike lane. They had to slam on their brakes in the middle of oncoming traffic lanes while I proceeded with my right of way. Wild that a bright yellow rain coat, front lights and pedal lights can be missed. We need more phone use regulation.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While riding with the flow of morning traffic and taking the lane (note: moving the same speed as traffic ahead) a woman aggressively swerved around me and cut me off, she was close enough for me to foot-check the side of her car. The driver proceeded to exit her vehicle at each of the next 3 intersections to yell at me and attempt to intimidate me. On one instance I had to dismount and maneuver my bike between myself and her. After this instance, I no longer ride without pepper spray.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: driver exiting the parking lot onto 6th Street and continued into the protected bike lane to make a right turn onto 6th. I doubt they saw me and there would have been a collision if the timing of our interaction was adjusted by a few seconds. They were at fault, but this is also an instance of difficult infrastructure design - a two-way bikeway on a one-way street. I was moving contraflow to vehicular traffic

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: rider ran a solid red light and was nearly hit by a driver exiting the garage on a green light. The rider had no lights.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Near right hook. Standard fare for this intersection

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: just your casual banking u-turn in the middle of uptown, with no turn signal. I figured they were pulling over so I move to the left to pass, but instead they turned left to do a u-turn. Nearly broadsided.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: near right hook. If I had not been keeping an eye out for negligent drivers from behind I easily would have hit directly from my left side.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: uber driver let their passenger off at the concrete barrier between vehicular traffic and the protected bike lane. The passenger disembarked with her head down, looking at their phone. I slowed but did not stop as they started walking right in front of me. They saw my lights and stepped out of the way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The rider was lane-splitting while performing a wheelie and cut into the intersection at a high rate of speed on a solid red. He very nearly hit a pedestrian in the crosswalk who had the right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver turning right into the parking garage paused to let me pass so that I would not be right-hooked. A driver leaving the parking garage misinterpreted this as that driver giving them space and time to leave so they started out right in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver took a right turn into into the protected bike line. Clearly a mistake, they had to back out so that I could continue. This is why we need bollards and not flex posts.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver parked in "protected" bike lane. I had to move into the vehicle lane to pass. The driver started to move as I was passing to their left and almost merged into me. (South Carolina license plate #: XEP-449, white Lexus hatchback)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver speeding south on Beatties Ford at well over 60mph hit the curb and flipped their car onto the sidewalk, hitting businesses on the west side of the street. I observed a cyclist on the sidewalk a few moments before the driver flipped their car.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Blared horn then near miss doing 50 mph in a 35. Driver turned then came back from behind to harass me. Kept asking where I lived. Early 90's Mazda or Honda Civic with white paint, rust spots.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Traveling northbound in the bike lane on 15-501, waited for a gap in traffic to cross the 15-501-54 ramp, found one but driver sped up and flew in front of me and cut me off.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing burning tree in the crosswalk with green (the pedestrian phase isn't protected so there's no reason to trigger it). A driver of a white SUV turned right on red from burning tree, directly across my path. I had to hit the brakes to avoid being run over. She never looked my way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was headed southeast on the greenway along NC 54. I had a pedestrian signal to cross over Burning Tree. A motorist who wanted to turn left onto Burning Tree had a permissive yellow, and saw a gap in on-coming motor vehicle traffic and scooted through it. He saw me in the crosswalk at the last minute and stopped, thankfully, even though it meant the on-coming traffic also had to stop to avoid T-boning the man trying to turn. 
This stupid permissive yellow is going to get someone killed.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was commuting on my bike and happened upon this accident minutes after it occurred.  

(You should include an option to report  incidents as an observer/bystander)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The driver of a large SUV came up behind me at high speed, swerved to get around me, then swerved back to avoid rear-ending a car in the next lane, almost clipping my front wheel. I was going about 20mph (it's a descent); the SUV driver was probably going 50 or more when he swerved toward me.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was approaching a stop light, preparing to turn left and positioned near the center of the lane (vehicles in that lane can turn left or right or go straight). The driver of a pickup truck pulling a wide trailer pulled up right beside me as we both came to a stop at the light. I saw the trailer in my mirror and noticed that if the truck pulled forward faster than I did when the light turned, the trailer would clip me from behind. So I moved over out of the travel lane just as the light turned.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A motorist attempted to pass me as we were both turning right at a 4-way stop; the motorist nearly hit an on-coming car head on and had to hit the brakes and swerve toward me to avoid a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A motorist passed me on a blind turn, drifting into the path of an on-coming cyclist, forcing the cyclist to swerve into a parking lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was turning left, after having clearly signaled. A motorist coming behind me passed me on the left just as I was beginning my turn.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turned left onto Morningside Drive as my son and I were in the intersection travelling north on N. Greensboro St. Lady claimed she did not see us. She had dark sunglasses on, so inattention more than glare is the likeliest reason.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: turning left from the Wilson Park bike trail onto Estes Drive. A driver of a Honda civic (couldn't see the license plate, plus the driver sped away from the scene) facing me and coming from Estes Park Apartments complex was turning right onto Estes Dr. He hit my right pedal with his bumper.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing Fordham on Willow, westbound, in the traffic lane with a green light.  A motorist attempted to turn right on red from SB Fordham onto Willow while I was still clearing the intersection. He came within a few feet of me before he heard my shouts and stopped.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My daughter and I were going straight down Elliot Rd. An elderly woman driving a Prius turned left from a sidestreet directly into our path. My daughter was on the back of my bike. I managed to brake and veer to avoid collision. The driver did not look our direction before pulling out, nor did she respond to my yelling.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Construction has eliminated all sidewalks from outside a grocery story, forcing all humans on foot or bike into the parking lot to enter the store. I was nearly backed into by two motorists while  trying to get through the parking lot on my bike. One only stoped when I smacked the back of her car with the side of my fist. I was only in that location because all safer alternatives had been blocked by the construction project.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding northeast on S Roxboro St, taking the lane since the bike lane ends shortly before here. A driver passed me on a blind corner, then saw oncoming traffic and merged back into my lane before fully passing me.

i_type: Fall
details: I was swerving to avoid hitting a hanging tree limb and fell into off the side into shrubbery and tree limbs on the Thermal Belt Rail Trail. The county needs to maintain the trails better. I haven't been biking since. (It's also been rainy and hot.)

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Passed on curve by semi, car approached in other direction. Semi came back in lane, forcing me to edge of shoulder.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver ran a stop sign nearly almost hitting cyclists in parking lot after the cyclist was at a stop sign.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The driver ran a stop sign on the small hill turning left go in front of the building nearly Al most hitting the cyclist that stopped. This parking lot is known for close calls failure to stop and yield to pedestrians crossing.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Hits patch of black ice that sent me into the guard rail at about 30 flipped over the rail hitting left arm causing me to spin into it fracturing my leg.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passed me in the vehicle lane, then made a right-hand turn in front of me without checking bike lane. I hit the passenger side and went down hard. I was able to roll with it, and the only injuries were my feet (toenails detached from getting jammed into the toes of my shoes). Speed at time of collision was approximately 25mph, since it was a downhill stretch.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Heading west on W 5th Avenue from Olentangy River Road, I waited for cars in the the left lane to pass so I could merge, as the right lane was ending soon. A bus was blocking the remainder of the lane, so I had to merge a bit early, just before the driveway entrance of the Speedway on the corner. After merging, I was suddenly struck by a car turning left into the Speedway. The driver remained at the scene and EMS was called. The entire front of the bicycle was damaged beyond repair.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver tried  to beat me to a stop sign I was approaching. He passed me left of center and then pulled into my lane as I arrived at the stop, nearly running me over. He was non-apologetic and aggressive, shouting at me to "share the road!"  A depraved indifference to human life; a homicidal person who should not be driving..

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Biking west on Hudson from I-71, crossed the 4th street intersection with the light. The bike lane stops at the intersection, and bikes have to merge with cars just as the road narrows. A car tried to pass me where there wasn't space; I had to stop to avoid being pushed into the curb or into a telephone pole.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking on the trail crossing when a car traveling too fast from the parking lot almost broadsided me.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was in the bike lane.  Person drove up next to me, and slowed so I thought they were slowing for me, but they turned into a driveway.  It was narrow and there was a curb so I fell over, but was not hit by the vehicle.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading south.  I crossed the Marys River on the multi-use bridge.  I approached Chapman, and there was a car waiting to pull out onto the highway.  The car was still rolling, and the driver was looking both ways.  He looked right at me and then his car stopped.  I took that as a sign to proceed, and I did.  Even though he looked at me, he clearly didn't actually see me because he pulled out while my bike was right in front of his car.  He hit me.  I think he collided with my pedal.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle initiated left turn from westbound Campus Wy onto southbound 26th without signal after I had entered intersection. Vehicle stopped before collision and we both continued.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle struck a bike causing some soreness to the bicyclist, who landed on the hood of the vehicle. The driver told the bicyclist he was going to park and instead drove away. Reported to CPD as hit-and-run.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Hit a big recycling container in the road flipped over and landed on my face almost got knocked out

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Guy in a truck on River Rd cut across oncoming traffic to try and hit me in the bike lane, turned around to follow me and tried to hit me again as his friend in the passenger seat yells that they're going to kill me as they passed

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver in car turning right on red from Southbound SE 82nd Ave / OR 213 onto Westbound SE Foster Rd did not see me coming through the intersection with a green light, despite high-vis jacket. Driver pulled out and I had to swerve left into potential traffic behind me. I yelled at the driver multiple times, and once they noticed me, they slowed down, and I was able to merge across their lane into the bike lane again.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of eastbound truck with red light turning right onto SE Foster Rd off of SE Holgate Blvd crashed into cyclist crossing Holgate in the crosswalk.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing the crosswalk northbound on the Gresham-Fairview Trail when a vehicle stopped in the westbound lane of Division Street for a pedestrian and myself in the crosswalk started going and crashed into me. The driver claimed that while she saw the pedestrian crossing, she didn't see me on my bicycle because of sun glare. It was cloudy that day.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passing me suddenly veered right across the bike lane without signaling.  I had to brake hard to avoid a collision. The driver swore at me and sped away.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding eastbound on Se Hawthorne. A car side-swiped me as it was passing, there was minimal traffic and it had a second lane available. The vehicle drove into Ladds, I followed; the driver initially stopped, then fled the area.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is just one example of a frequent problem at this location with drivers turning right without yielding to cyclists going straight... even though the intersection is marked with a large green box and signage.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading north on 181st and crossing Burnside on a green light when the driver of a vehicle to my right made a right on red without stopping into me. This threw me across into another lane of traffic and damaged my bicycle to the point where I could not continue my trip.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Heading to work, right hooked while in the bike lane by a lifted pickup who didn't signal. Driver stopped to give insurance information. Had to go to urgent care and couldn't work for two days, took months to fully recover. Claim denied by his insurance, responsible for several thousand in medical bills and damage to bike/clothing.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cyclist ran the light, was hit by truck in northbound lane. Driver came to a stop shortly after the collision, so no secondary impact.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was traveling Eastbound in bike lane going into the shared Right Turn Only lane to connect to bikeway on other side of 12th St. Bridge. Car Driver approached from behind very aggressively, honking and taking both hands off the wheel to flip me off upon my raising a hand to communicate "What's the issue". I slowed down and the driver was not paying attention to my speed and almost collided with me. Came less than a foot from my rear wheel and swerved around me.  Signaling Right w/ Lights on bike.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Right huge by a huge pickup. Signaled about 1 second before starting her turn into a driveway. Video here: https://youtu.be/VUahpNlrx8Q

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Right-hooked by a city truck who didn't bother to look or signal. Did absolutely nothing to help. A cop who happened to be in the area showed up but refused to file a report. Smashed my helmet, had to get several x-rays/scans and am down $2k+ so far in bike/clothing damage and medical expenses

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver headed westbound on Simpson turned left directly into rider headed east.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Intentionally side swiped me on willamette and then slowed down so he could try and hit me again. Only stopped when I started filming. Old white dude in a black Acura, license plate OR HQQS

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver honked and yelled at me while passing too closely, even though there was ample room to pass and no other traffic. He didn't appreciate my hand gesture and swerved right to cut me off. I veered left toward the centerline to avoid his vehicle, and he again swerved to obstruct my path.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: More than once, cars turning left (south) from 24th onto Willamette fail to yield to bikes. My take is that they are trying to quickly get left turn in before light changes and don't pay attention to bikes crossing in front of them.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Very unfilled gap road. Caused me to slip over bike and hurt Over myself. Road was filled IN with water so i didn’t see the ditch

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: hit-and-run, driver approached from behind at high speed, entered bike lane and struck me on their passenger side, then continued turning right and did not stop or slow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car almost hit because they were driving IN bike lane driving

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver refused to follow behind bicycle taking lane with less than 4 feet to pass. Illegally squeezed past on left, passenger rolled down window and poured water on me, hit me with passenger side of vehicle, turned right on West Oxford and drove away.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My friend and I were biking on a very quiet street. A car was stopped ahead, driver talking to someone in his yard. A fast gray mini drove behind us, passed dangerously close, and then drove around the stopped car and partially onto the lawn on which the person was standing in order to drive past.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Elderly female turning right into a parking lot hit me as I was crossing over the entrance. She said she never saw me dispute my front blinking bike and front helmet light as well as bright clothing. It was Memorial Day weekend and she was in a rush to get a  parking space!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: car ran a stop sign while on their phone and hit me (who did not have a stop sign)

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: 11 pm in front of 5 Guys restaurant, I am heading West, car coming opposite direction, turns left without slowing down into parking lot with no turning signal, I had yellow vest and flashing headlights, brought no notice to guy on phone, I go flying over roof and land hard on concrete... Major surgery to right shoulder....

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
This was not me but a person died so it should be on this map.
