details: Crossing yield access to Pembina at Dalhousie with shoulder check carefully done.    Vehicle crossed from centre lane into my path.   I fell off my bike and sustained bruises and scrapes.    Driver stopped to see if I needed help.   No assistance required.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was cycling southbound in the Pembina painted bike lane when a vehicle exited a nearby parking lot and began driving slowly in the curb lane slightly in front of me, before coming to a complete stop ahead of the entrance to the gas station. Believing they had seen me and were waiting for me to pass I began to pass the van, only for the driver to begin completing its turn. I was forced to stop completely, at which point the driver stopped as well and I completed my pass.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding northbound on the active transportation path, each vehicle turning right from Clarence Ave onto Waverley St ran the stop sign or stopped across the active transportation path forcing me to stop to avoid being hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding northbound on the active transportation path when I observed a box truck proceeding westbound on Clarence Ave towards Waverley St at a rate of speed that suggested that the driver would not be stopping. In anticipation of this I slowed my pace to avoid being hit by the driver who proceeded to run the stop sign and turn right onto Waverley St.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Driver blew through the stop sign and bike path crossing nearly resulting in a collision. Intersection is poor. High speed vehicles turning, stop sign set very far back from curb, no signage or road paint indicating a bike path crossing.

This happens every single day due to poor intersection design

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding southbound on the Waverley path towards Clarence Ave when I noticed an SUV proceeding westbound on Clarence without decelerating to stop at the stop sign, rather the driver ran the stop sign across the multiuse path requiring me to stop to avoid being struck. Drivers frequently stop across the path or run the stop sign to enter Waverley St at speed.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A truck accelerated closely past me and the driver revved his engine loudly. I displayed disapproval and when we stopped at the next light, he yelled at me and asked if I had a problem. I did, and told him I didn't appreciate how close and fast he was driving.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Going SB Dakota in middle lane and was cut off by vehicle turning right to go to St Vital mall.

Sharrows have not been repainted all summer.  I have complained to city but no response so far.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding northbound on Pembina towards Crescent Dr and came within inches of being right hooked by a turning vehicle while turning right. The turning vehicle turned across the bike lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My fiancee and I were cycling westbound on Crescent Dr past several parked cars when we were aggressively passed by a pickup truck hauling a trailer (likely because the driver needed to wait to pass us due to oncoming traffic).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading northbound on Pembina when a right-turning vehicle entered the intersection as I was approximately 10 meters away from it. Managed to avoid serious damage to myself or the bike, however the rear rim needed to be replaced.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car cut in front of me and turned right, just as I was approaching intersection. Had to brake hard to avoid collision. Don't know if driver just not paying attention, didn't care, or misjudged distance.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: cycling northbound on south drive in the process of passing a parked car outside of the door zone. oncoming traffic was another cyclist followed by 2 vehicles, the first vehicle close squeezed between both cyclists to pass the cyclist they were following and the 2nd swerved towards me and cursed at me because I was apparently taking up to much space on the road. Young blonde haired male in an older model red pickup truck.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding westbound on the McGillivray path when a vehicle making an illegal right turn off McGillivray into the shopping centre parking lot one-way exit lane onto McGillivray honked and cursed at me for not giving way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cycling southbound on Pembina past Windermere where the bike lane ends and merges into the curb lane. Had to slam on the breaks to avoid being struck by a vehicle driving in the curb lane as there is literally no where for cyclists to go.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This happens frequently in this location. I cross by bicycle from Windermere Ave. to Point Rd, something I do because the bike lane ends here. The road is designed in such a way that any traffic turning left leave no room for oncoming traffic who _always_ swerve onto the wrong side of the road meaning they head into any bicyclists crossing. It is incredibly dangerous.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Nearly right hooked in the southbound bike lane by a car turning into the 7-11 parking lot.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As I was travelling north through the intersection a car driver blew through the stop sign and hit my bike. I have a broken wrist and will stop cycling for the remainder of the year.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was on the shared path and I had the go signal, but a truck on the street parallel to me made a left turn towards me (crossing the intersection). The truck did not even bother to slow down.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding westbound on the Harte Trail when I noticed an off leash dog (against Winnipeg bylaws) standing near its owner. As I passed them the dog gave chase and was parallel to my bike and nearly swerved into me. I increased my speed and was able to distance myself from the dog.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
i was heading southbound on the shaftesbury bike path. I knew the path ended at wilkes, but the light was green, so i went through the little island (crossing through the yield) into the northbound traffic lane. As i started north through the intersection, the light changed to yellow, and I realized a car was turning left as the yellow was goin to change to red.
She braked. I braked, and the car that was (illegally) entering the intersection after her ALSO braked.
We all stopped w/o coliding

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Stopped at the corner of Planet and Parker waiting to turn right when a left turning orange Jeep making the opposite turn from Parker to Planet cut the corner and nearly struck me. They likely cut the corner to be able to make the turn faster than at the 90 degrees required if they had stayed in their lane.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Driver exited parked vehicle parked on west side of Cambridge St without checking for cyclists. I would have been doored had I not been cycling slightly outside of the door zone.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding WB on the Taylor multiuse path approaching Nathaniel St when I noticed a vehicle approaching the intersection from the mall intending to turn right onto Taylor across the multiuse path. I stopped despite having a green light as the driver appeared to intend to roll through the red light and did not check the multiuse path for cyclists/pedestrians. Eventually they stopped and I proceeded through the intersection, at which point I noticed the driver had their cellphone in hand making a call

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding in the Harrow St bike lane towards Taylor Ave when a distracted driver turning left from either Carter or Hector turned into the bike lane forcing me to stop to avoid being hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding southbound on Harrow through Grant Ave in the right turn/sharrow when a vehicle in the left turn/through lane cut me off to move around a left turning vehicle. Had I not anticipated and braked I would have been struck.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I arrived at a small traffic circle from the east and entered the intersection at a good speed (~15km/hr). A vehicle approached from the north approach (too my right meaning I had the right-of-way) and did not slow approaching the traffic circle. Luckily I cleared just before the vehicle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Left turning vehicle nearly hit me by rolling a 3-way stop. I had the right of way. They honked at me when I held up an index finger to remind them that I had stopped at the intersection first.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding in the northbound bike lane on Pembina Highway when I needed to stop suddenly to avoid being hit by a GFL garbage truck that was turning left from southbound Pembina Highway onto Calrossie Blvd.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound SUV driver on Pembina Hwy ran a red at the pedestrian/cycling crossing at Calrossie Blvd. The driver had exited the Jubilee Overpass when the light changed, traffic was clear and the light had been red for several seconds by the time the driver passed. As I did not observe them braking for the light I did not leave the curb to cross the street until they had passed.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding on Riverside Dr towards Jubilee Ave, was closely passed by a pickup truck (firefighter plates) at the intersection of Merriam Blvd. The driver made no attempt to stop at the 3-way stop sign at the intersection of Merriam Blvd and Riverside Dr.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
I was cycling up the hill onto the Dunkirk pathway after exiting the tunnel under Osborne to proceed southbound when I cut off a southbound cyclist who was proceeding from the north forcing them to come to an immediate stop. Fortunately no one was injured.

They had the right of way, however the design of these intersecting pathways could use improvement.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cyclist was exiting a driveway to turn left onto the road and failed to see by approach (possibly due to parked cars on the side of the road where I was travelling/she was crossing, however I was riding at a safe distance from these on the road). There was no time to avoid the collision, except to yell "heads up!"  Ended up t-boning the other cyclist as they crossed perpendicularly into my lane of travel, they were knocked from their bicycle but did not sustain any injuries.

i_type: Fall
details:
At t junction of the asphalt bike path, I was turning north. I had slowed down. My bike slid out from under me and I crashed on my left side, contacting knee, hand and ribcage to asphalt and skidding to a stop. This happened suddenly and I had no ability to adjust. 

There was light rain. The path had recently been resurfaced with a protective coating. The path is much smoother with the new coating vs. prior years.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Porsche Macan driver was  looking down to their right while approaching bike crossing I was entering. They looked up just in time to brake, I also braked and I was not hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was waiting to cross Jubilee northbound on Cockburn. The light changed and we were about to proceed through the intersection when an SUV on eastbound Jubilee changed lanes from behind a vehicle stopped at the light and ran the red light. Fortunately we noticed the driver running the light and stopped our progress in order to avoid being hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Pulling to the stop sign on mixed-use trail, another cyclist turns from the street onto the trail at a very quick speed, we nearly crash head-on. The hedges on the West side of the trail makes it very hard to see incoming traffic from the street. And additionally the stop sign is further ahead than the trail, which makes situations with cars extremely dangerous.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car passed close enough to make by bike wobbly (within arms-length), even with a clear lane available to give me the appropriate amount of space.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Dismounted bike,  waited to cross street at the lights. Proceeded to walk my bike across the street when it was my turn, only to have a car turning left almost run me over. I jumped out of the way while he still drove around me. Autumnwood and Archibald lights.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: painted bike lane passes through a bus stop. As the bike lane rises up to sidewalk level at those spots and curves around a bus stop ‘island’ extension where people waiting for the bus can stand or sit. Unfortunately, due to a lack of physical separation, people waiting for the bus often stand in the bike lane and are uncertain where to safely stand in face of approaching cyclists. At this particular bus stop the bus shelter opens directly onto the bike lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding northbound in the Pembina bike lane in from of Accurate Lawn and Garden Equipment when a truck exiting their parking lot proceeded towards the bike lane without indicating they were going to stop and/or check the bike lane for people on bikes. I needed to shout out to alert them to my presence, which let them to stop and respect my right of way.

i_type: Fall
details:
Approached a gravel pathway that has a sharp turn at the top of a hill; when making the inside turn, back tire lost traction and I wiped out.  Slid partway down the hill on the gravel.  No other bikes involved. I have taken that path daily for six years (I commute by bike from May-October), without incident.
I was traveling faster than usual and the gravel was very loose.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Vehicle cut in front of me and stopped abruptly to avoid hitting a pedestrian. I ran into the back of car and landed on another car.
MPI then sent me a bill for all damages.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Near Miss someone not stopping at the stop sign...

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Two-way bike lane ends at Warsaw however some cyclists continue southbound in what is now a narrow northbound lane endangering northbound cyclists.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Run off the road (again) by a tractor-trailer. Would have been run over if I hadn't swerved off the pavement, driver did not move over at all. Couldn't see company name.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Watched dark blue commercial vehicle (tractor/trailer) approach from behind in my mirror, was not moving over at all. I had to swerve off the road onto the unpaved muddy shoulder to avoid being hit. Driver did not move over at all until after he was beside me and I was off the road.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of a light coloured sedan 1st 3 plate #'s CN7 passed within inches, despite no oncoming traffic & everyone else in same direction moving over.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

I yelled to get his attention and I slowed down.  Driver apologized and claimed he didn't see me, despite my wearing a bright jacket and with a with light on the handle bars.  Driver's brain likely in a fog and not prepared to see anything smaller than another car or truck.

i_type: Fall
details:

was on his way home from a 40-kilometre bicycle ride May 8 when he struck a curb on 24 Avenue near 166 Street.

Rogers told Peace Arch News Sunday that the collision sent him over his handlebars. He struck his head on the pavement, “fortunately I was wearing a helmet,” he got road rash on his legs and arms, broke his glasses and broke his collarbone.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: On number of occasions, vehicles did not come to a full stop at intersection of quiet rural road , & had to hit the brakes to avoid t-boning/hitting me, despite my wearing bright clothing and having flashing white light on handlebars.   Drivers are conditioned to look for large moving objects and not cyclists.  MVA advise to stay as far to right as practical not practical in a rural setting.  Take-the-lane to be seen, to avoid potholes/road debris and squirrels suddenly running out unto road.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: S&K gravel truck turned out of queen  into my lane forcing me to stop to avoid being run over.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of white van with VanPro sign leaving driveway. Stopped @ sidewalk, looked at me, waited, then pulled out right in front of me. Had to skid to a stop to avoid crashing.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

Sustained bruising to left leg and elbow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver on Clearbrook turned right onto SFW from slip lane into space I was occupying. I had to swerve into other lane to avoid being hit. Driver looked right at me and did not react at all. Wearing hi-vis, lights on.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle was heading north on Janzen Street and turned west into a driveway directly in my path with no signal.  No time to react or avoid the vehicle.  Hit the passenger front fender, launched over the hood and impacted the windshield with my left shoulder, and head.  Suffered lots of bruising, glass cuts on two fingers and bike and helmet were totaled.  EMS were on site and police incident report was filed.  Still waiting for ICBC claim to be processed (2019/09/12).

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of silver minivan plate#px626b pulled out of parking row right into my path and never saw me. Lights and Hivis. Stopped hard right beside driver door. Banged on window to alert driver she almost hit me. Not paying any attention.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Travelling south a northbound driver of a convertible car decided to pass a line of cars and drove into my lane and forced me off the road.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
This road has no paved shoulder for cyclists, so I was riding approximately one foot from the road edge. A car passed by me squeezing between me and the center line of the road. The car passed by with about one foot between me and the car. The car did not slow down when passing. If I had to swerve to avoid a rock or pothole in the road I would have been hit by the car.
There was no traffic coming in the opposite direction, the car could have easily used the other lane to pass by me!

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

Driver of B&B Construction flatbed, stopped at the stop sign, decided that he was not going to wait for me to complete my turn and drove into the space I was about to occupy, in order to beat the traffic.  If I hadn't anticipated this dumb-a_ _ move, and applied the brakes, I would have slammed into the side of the vehicle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver of LX5618 followed close behind, couldn't pass due to 1 oncoming car. i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: It is risky to get onto and off of the bridge crossing between Mission and Abbotsford on the Mission side. There is a stretch where you have to ride on Highway 11 and the drivers are not respectful of cyclists. In this case, a large black pickup swerved deliberately towards me and blared its horn to scare me while passing. I was on the shoulder, not the road.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding eastbound on 7th Avenue in the bike lane when I approached Horne Street. Two cars were stopped at the stop sign for Horne, and one was turning right to go westbound on 7th. As I passed, the car turning right pulled out and clipped my rear wheel and I fishtailed, eventually falling to the ground.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a dangerous intersection because there are no traffic controls or warning to motorists that they are approaching a bicycle crossing.  This is on the Lakes Bike route which is well travelled and we use it on a daily basis twice a day (on the way to work and then on the way home).  It crosses Imperial Ave, a busy road.  Often the only way to cross is when a considerate motorist sees our dilemma and stops to let us pass or to wait for a break in the flow or traffic and to scoot across.

I had to brake hard in order to avoid slamming into the drivers side of the vehicle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking southbound on the sea-to-river bikeway and several vehicles passed me within inches. It is on a slope, so a lot of motorists becomes frustrated with the slow bikes and pass extremely closely.  Due to the parked cars and width of the road, it is not safe for any cars to pass a cyclist. The city has to do something here, at the very least a "Take the lane" or "Single-file" sign to make it clear that motorists should not pass.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Fall

Lost control of bicycle, went down on right side and slid for approx 5-10 meters into curb on right side. Significant road rash on leg, arm, and hands.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While heading Eastbound uphill a vehicle decided to pass me on the left just as I was passing a parked car at the crest of an uphill. I had approximately 1.5 ft space to my right from the parked car, and the passing car passed at >30km with approximately 1.0 ft of margin, despite my bike's flashing rear light and a toddler visibly seated in a rear-mounted bike seat. The driver gave no indication of any caution or care for the manoeuvre.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle travelling south on Wayburne in right turn lane moved all the way into the marked ped/bike crossing before stopping the car. The driver almost hit me as I was on the crossing heading west. The driver failed to stop before entering the intersection before making his right turn.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle

i_type: Fall

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: There is a right turn lane left of the bike lane here. I'm always on the watch when waiting at the light for what's coming on this lane behind me. In this incident, a dump truck with a trailer pulled up next to me. I horned (have a very loud airhorn) to let him know I was there. He just horned in seeming annoyance and insisted on taking his left turn, his truck and trailer swinging dangerously close to me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: At westbbound Lougheed Highway intersection with North Road a dump truck with pup trailer pulled up in the right-turn lane next to the bike lane with its wheels in the bike lane leaving me hardly any room and proceeded to turn right on redLuckily the SUV on my left let me pull up in front of them and out of the way of the truck. The next day in exactly the same spot another dump truck and trailer pulled up in the right turn lane but stopped 10 feet behind me at the red light and let me go first.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding in the bike lane when a car beside me steered into the bike lane as I was passing it on the right. I hit the side-mirror of the car with my arm and managed to dismount my bicycle without falling/crashing. Cars often drive in the bike lane here to bypass traffic and get to the right turn lane more quickly.

i_type: Fall

This has been a hazard for years.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle stopped directly in the crosswalk while I had a green light to cross, the pedestrian sound was beeping and I was ringing my bell and trying to catch the driver's attention. The driver was only looking to their left to check for oncoming traffic. I tapped the front hood of their car twice and proceeded in front of their car, at which time they moved forward to turn and I fell with my bike as they drove into me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

because a driver couldn't be bothered to stop at the stop sign and then proceed across the elephants' feet crossing of the Willingdon Urban Trail.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

Both bikes were undamaged. *Taking a wide turn into the park is common due to poor road conditions at the corner & speed from hill.*

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

I yelled back at him since he had almost hit me and he got out and ran at me on foot , threatening me when I tried to read his license plate. I was able to ride off quickly without him catching me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle

The handle on the bollard caught my rear rack and stopped my bike sending me flying.  Required emergency visit and stitches on my face.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle

I went out into the intersection (wearing bright red poncho on bright sunny day with clear hand signal) and when car didn’t go, I turned left. Suddenly the car moved forwards at high speed then stopped. Then started again and stopped 2cm from front wheel.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car turning right on to 17th avenue specifcally sped up and then slowed down and veered into my path as they went to turn. I was nearly run off the road because of them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver on Watson drove through stop sign as I was exiting plaza on 14th and  nearly hit me. I was able to react and brake in time.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passed me extremely closely squeezing in between me & oncoming traffic. About 30cm between me & his van. Then he pulled over & yelled obscenities at me after passing me closely.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Another cyclist travelling northbound on Watson street crossed in front of me as I was travelling east on 14th Ave. I couldn't stop in time & hit his back wheel. There was a car stopped in the intersection that was partly blocking his view.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Pedestrians DO NOT obey their signals when crossing on the east side of Main and 14th, in front of the outdoor seating area. I was coming through the intersection on a green light when one randomly started to wander through. I wasn't in danger of hitting him, but I ride through this intersection almost every day, and the problem seems to be getting worse.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As I was riding eastbound out of the protected bike lane on 14th Ave a northbound driver on Watson rolled through the stop sign & almost hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver didn't stop at the stop sign on Watson, nearly hit me as I was riding through from the protected hike lane beside the plaza to 14th Ave.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver on Watson street failed to stop at the 2-way stop, so i had to hit my brakes despite having right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As I was riding west through the intersection of Sophia & 14th, an Eastbound driver turned left in front of me, forcing me to slam on my brakes to avoid the collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Eastbound driver passed me extremely closely as another vehicle was coming westbound. About 15-20cm from my elbow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound pickup driver rolled theough the stop sign at 14th Ave without looking right in front of me as I was entering the intersection. I had to hit my brakes to avoid a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver rolled through stop sign southbound on Watson street & didn't look until they were in the middle of the intersection, blocking my path. I had to brake to avoid hitting them.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound van rolled through stop sign & nearly hit me as I was travelling through the intersection eastbound.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver rolled through the red light to turn from southbound on Main to westbound on 14th Ave as I was riding though the intersection. I had to brake to avoid hitting his truck.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Eastbound Driver passed me extremely closely from behind, with only about 20-30cm space.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound driver on Min street ran red light as I was already proceeding into the intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver slowed down (but didn't completely stop) at stop sign on Quebec at 14th and cut across my path on 14th, causing me to have to brake. This has actually happened many times at this intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Pickup truck driver turned right from Main to 14th Ave in front of me as I was travelling east on 14th through Main Street. He had a red light but didn't look to see me coming through the intersection. I had to brake to avoid hitting him.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking my kids to school with one on my cargobike & the other on her bike beside me. A large pickup truck towing a wide trailer came up behind us, honked at us, then passed us very closely--maybe 30cm between my elbow & his trailer.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver crossing 14th at Watson just drove across 14th like I wasn`t there in the roadway. Not the first time this has happened. I had to brake suddenly for crash avoidance. Could have turned out badly,

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver who was travelling behind me attempted to pass just before we reached the traffic circle, but didn't have enough space and chose to tailgate me and my children instead until we passed the traffic circle at Ontario St.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passed me at well over the speed limit (I was going 30) with maybe 12" of space from my elbow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Westbound (oncoming) vehicle passed me very closely (15-30 cm) after turning very fast onto 14th from Ontario.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Eastbound driver insisted on passing me with 20-30cm to spare in the narrowest part of the 14th Ave car canyon. Then he had to stop at the traffic circle anyway. Saved himself at least five seconds by endangering my life!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was turning left around a circular median, signalled but collided with a cyclist who had gone through the intersection on the wrong side of the median

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound SUV driver on Manitoba failed to stop at two-way stop & nearly hit me as I was going through the intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As I was riding west on 14th into the intersection, yet another driver rolled through the two way stop, northbound on Manitoba to westbound on 14th Ave, right in front of me. There were oncoming cyclists as well, so the driver then braked, stopping right in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: My 6yo, riding on the sidewalk, was narrowly missed as he entered the crosswalk by a car turning right at speed. He would have been hit except a pedestrian grabbed him and physically pulled him back.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver didn't stop at the stop sign on Manitoba, only saw me & stopped once they were in the middle of the intersectiom, blocking my way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver on Manitoba rolled through the stop sign & nearly hit me as I was riding east through the intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turning east onto 14thdrove through stop sign without stopping and nearly turned left into me as if they didn't see me. I had to swerve into curb lane before they realised and stopped.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver didn't see me until they nearly hit me in the traffic circle as I was most of the way through the intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver on North side of 14th Ave pulled out of parking space in front of me. I was going quite fast from the downhill & had to swerve to avoid hitting them. They didn't stop & later passed another cyclist extremely closely two blocks farther down the street.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Aggressive female Lexus driver tried to pass me IN the traffic circle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver failed to yield to me in traffic circle and did a right turn in front of my while I was IN traffic circle before them, forcing me to brake for crash avoidance.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver backed his pickup truck out of a driveway into the road as I was coming, he wasn't looking behind him & didn't respond at all to my electronic bike horn, I had to swerve to avoid him.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle turning right didn't check their blind spot.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Large SUV blew right through the red light travelling northbound on Nanaimo street, did not appear to even notice the red light.  Multiple cyclists and pedestrians entering the intersection East-West - thankfully everyone was on alert and noticed the egregious display of driving incompetence.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Proceeding through intersection on a green light.  Other cyclists were ahead of me and oncoming in other lane.  Southbound car failed to stop at the red light. I swerved and accelerated out of the way missing being hit by cms.  Yelled to warn oncoming riders who stopped in time to avoid collision.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was proceeding through Nanaimo on a green light. Traffic on Nanaimo heading south was backed up, causing some cars to block the intersection for east bound bikes and pedestrians. Those cars blocked my view of the northbound lane. A car went through the red light.

i_type: Fall
details: I was riding around a roundabout and hit a patch of black ice and lost control. I should have been going slower for the conditions.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding west on the Central Valley Greenway and a driver turned his vehicle left from Graden Drive onto the greenway without yielding, despite his having a stop sign and my having the right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was cycling west along the Central Valley Greenway.  At the intersection of Renfrew the button for cyclists to push to activate the lights is a few meters back from where the pedestrians cross.  The light was green for me to cycle straight across the intersection, but a car pointing northward was turning right on his red light, into Hebb Ave and was only looking to his left when turning. He drove in front of me cutting me off so that I had to stop for him.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Crossing Renfrew St in the crosswalk. Got hit by car turning left.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver was parked curbside infront of Tim Hortons and turned out of his spot without checking, driving the front of his car into my bike front tire/frame and leg. I flew over the handlebars. He did not accept fault, things I was 'travelling too fast' and 'should have been on the bikepath'.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As has happened many times to me and others I have observed, drivers turning left off Hebb onto Renfrew (S-bound) fail to check for pathway users approaching above walking speed Westbound along CVG.  A no Left turn or limited Left turn arrow here would mitigate a very dangerous intersection for CVG users.  I've seen/experienced this happening to cyclists, runners, scooter riders,skateboarders, rolle-rbladers and others.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Transit bus ran a stale red light, as I was starting into the intersection. I was able to move back out of the way. I have had many issues with cars running redlights, trying to cross Kingsway.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Heading south on Lakewood drive, after passing a parked van approaching the ‘entrance’ to Trout Lake, another cyclist appeared from the back alley heading eastbound turning left to go north on lakewood. I had to perform a hard brake to not collide with the cyclist already halfway turned toward Lakewood. The other cyclist was not peturbed or apologetic at having almost caused a collision.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading northbound on Lakewood Dr. I had entered the intersection and was going around the roundabout. There was a silver subaru outback (2014-2019 gen) plate 727 WLJ that was heading westbound along East 13th Ave. I have 3 headlights (1 solid and 2 flashing). I slow down to a stop because the vehicle appeared to be going fast and was not sure if they would stop. I'm already halfway through the intersection. Car stops for a moment and then proceeds even though I have the right of way.

i_type: Fall
details: I witnessed this. I saw an e-bike rider brushing off after a crash. The rider said someone driving a car-2-go ran the stop sign and he bailed out to the right hitting the curb, and skinning his elbow. The driver didn't stop to help out.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I got squeezed by a car turning right from 12th Ave onto Windsor with a parked car on my right. Once the turning car cleared me, the driver of the parked car opened his door, hitting my right leg, and knocked me off the saddle. I rode away but developed a massive bruise on my right thigh.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car was illegally turning left, was unable to stop.

i_type: Fall
details: NA

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:

Article content

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Westbound Driver decided to pass me, squeezing in between me & an oncoming vehicle. The driver's side mirrors were about 20cm from my handlebars.

i_type: Fall
details: Slipped on ice or frost while riding straight. Fell onto roadway. Scraped & bruised.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound driver ran a stale red light as I was starting into the intersection. We both slammed on the brakes & he had to swerve to not hit me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver (probably using church parking lot to rat run) failed to stop at stop sign, then stopped in front of me in the middle of the intersection as I was riding through.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver started to turn left (I assume into the parking lot at the church?) from parking lane on north side of street as I was passing. He didnt signal or look before turning & I had to shout so hed stop.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver turned left out if the Catholic school driveway almost into me. I had to swerve into the parking lane to avoid being hit.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I met a Mercedes at the intersection (with a stop sign), we looked at each other, and they went across Heather right at me (sort of a chicane left, then right, they didn't use a signal either)! I had to brake hard to avoid and they braked too.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver in and SUV did not stop at the stop sign on 13th, heading west, and instead creeped in front of my path as I headed south on Yukon and had the right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was in a traffic calming circle, and the driver of a sedan that entered it after me from the right made no indication of stopping.  I braked hard, and the squeak got the drivers attention, who was looking the other way and was resting her head in her hand. She said sorry through the open window.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: There are pillars, not well visible from bigger distance and without any horizontal warnings or signs. I was checking my gear shifting for few seconds and suddenly hit them, falling off completely uncontrolled.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was the cyclist approaching this intersection with a mass of skytrain riders crossing the shared pedestrian/cycle path. I almost hit a pedestrian who was texting on their phone one day and another day two pedestrians darted from the skytrain to cross the crosswalk and I almost hit them. During high traffic times, this area becomes very congested with pedestrians and it does not make sense to have a greenway cutting through it.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Hit and Run. 911 called.

Biking northbound on Gilmour bike path and entered intersection. A van did not stop at the stop sign and I collided with the side of the van. My heavy cargo bike with a solid front basket made a large impact and dent in the side of the van door. Vehicle slowed after impact and then drove off. 

The driver did not stop or look for cyclists or pedestrians while crossing the multiuse path.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car didn't stop at the stop sign nor look either direction while exiting the Costco parking lot. I was biking through the crossing when they drove straight in front of me without looking or stopping.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Rang bell and passed a cyclist in front of me, in the oncoming lane (there was no oncoming bike or ped traffic).
The cyclist made a sharp left-turn maneuver (perhaps to pull over on the north side of the path). Biker cut me off and collided with the front of my bike.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
At slow speed and on the right side of the path, I turned right from SB Rupert to WB CVG. As I turned the corner, an oncoming cyclists traveling at high speed and on the wrong side of the path came speeding towards me. I couldn't move over any more, and our pedals collided. The rider lost control and almost went straight into traffic on Rupert.

Cyclist at fault was apparently passing pedestrians and did not wait for a safe space to complete the maneuver or move back into her own lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Blind corner from Rupert to westbound CVG. Nearly collided with a ped as I was turning right. She was walking on the north side of the path, which was the wrong side for her. Blind corner makes it hard to see what's ahead.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car heading S on Lakewood failed to stop at Stop sign.  Myself and a second cyclist were travelling W on CVG.  I was turning Left other rider proceeding straight.  Car slowed, looked at us them proceeded regardless.  I swerved hard and pulled beside the car, other rider swerved behind.  Driver swore at me when I pointed out the stop sign.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Southbound driver failed to yield to me though i was already in the intersection. I had to slam on my brakes to avoid being sideswiped or t-boned. She didnt even seem to notice me at all despite my extremely bright headlight.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
SUV left turn on a green when I was passing through intersection, also green light for me.  I had right of way.  Was going ~35kmh on my bike, slammed brakes when I saw the car turn, made contact with their vehicle near back right wheel, then I fell over on my left side.

Spoke with the driver after, said I was unharmed outside of a small scrape, her reasoning was she didn't see me, sun was in her eyes.  Didn't go any further since no damage to the car, me, or my bike.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound on Main, just crossed 12th when a van sped up on my left side, swerved in front of me, and slammed on their brakes to take a quick right turn into the gas station parking lot (rather than wait behind me). I slammed on my brakes, skidded, my front wheel bumped the side/back of the van.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver exited laneway to cross Ontario Street without checking oncoming traffic, said she "didn't see" me

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Westbound bike lane is separated from traffic, but vehicles turn into mall parking lot across bike lane. East bound car turned into lot as I crossed the driveway, and I was hit by his front bumper, drivers side. Thrown off my bike, bumps and bruises, bent front wheel.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car heading South on Lakewood failed to stop at Stop sign and I only avoided collision by turning into Northbound (oncoming) lane of Lakeview.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car travelling N on Lakewood failed to stop at Stop sign (2-way Stop) and nearly hit 2 cyclists approaching the intersection along the bike way (who have right of way).  Both cyclists had good front lights, I was approx 50M away and saw both clearly before the incident.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car heading South on Lakeview stopped at Stop sign then proceeded regardless of oncoming cyclists (2 others in addition to myself).  I was turning onto Lakeview so avoided collision by tightening my turn and shouted to warn other riders behind me who were able to slow and swerve behind the vehicle

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: I was stopped waiting for light to turn green. A person on an electric unicycle a little ways in front of me first travelled in a circle then stopped a short distance in front of me then proceeded to back into my bike. This was fairly jarring but I managed to keep my bike upright.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle turned right on a red light, despite the no right on red sign. Vehicle turning from Still Creek onto Gilmour (southbound) was surprised to see a bike in crosswalk. The driver slammed on their brakes at the last minute missing me by inches. I was biking northbound through the crossing with elephant feet with a walk signal.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: An aggressive driver was attempting to turn right on a red light (despite the sign indicating no right turn on red). He was on Still Creek turning right on Gilmour. I was travelling northbound on the Gilmour multiuse path. The driver saw me at the last minute and berated me for cycling the "wrong way". He was not aware that this is a two-way bike route or that there is no right turn on a red.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: White mini-van had pulled a U-turn on N Grandview & Lakewood and appeared to be waiting for the cyclist and myself to pass.  Just as the cyclist ahead of me drew level they drove forward missing her only because she swerved and braked hard.  Minivan then continued N on Lakeview.  Cyclist resumed her journey.  This intersection suffers one of the greatest dangers for cyclists, the parent driven minivan.  I hope the driver was completely distracted and didn't intentionally try to hit the rider.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Almost t-boned a blind gray mercedes who ran the stop sign going northbound. I forgot  whether it was at 2pm or 9pm as I had multiple rides that day.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: As i was riding North on Fraser Street a driver turned out of a laneway on the east side of the street to go North. He didnt see me at all & i couldnt swerve enough or stop in time, so i hit the back end of his car & then fell into the street.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car heading west on E 10th Ave took an illegal left turn onto Commercial Dr southbound and nearly hit me as I was crossing Commercial Dr on E 10th Ave eastbound while the walk sign was on.  Both the car and I came to a full stop about 1 meter apart.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car ran a red light at a pedestrian / bike crossing and hit me side on.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle came up from behind me close, honking to get out of the way. I pulled to the side and it sped past me. The roadway is very narrow with two-sided auto parking. Car should not have approached so closely or tried to squeeze by.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The guy was making an illegal U-turn and didn’t even signal so I slammed my breaks and wasn’t in time so I fell.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was going straight along heather across 12th with a green light. The driver of an oncoming car turned left across my path, and I had to brake hard to avoid. The driver did not signal the turn, but he flashed his high beams at me as he was turning.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: On Yukon and 10th, second accident witnessed this summer. Cyclist struck by moving vehicle. Ambulance and police called and attended..

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: On a green light I crossed Clark on 10th, heading East, and a pick up truck ran a red light (heading north) and nearly hit me. Driver had to break real hard and came to a stop ~20cm from me. This is not the first time I see a car run a red light at this intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: There was a green light for cyclists to cross the Clark intersection along 10th avenue, and luckily I paused at the median because there was a pickup truck that went through their red light at 10th ave, travelling approximately 60km/hr.  Would have gotten hit if I didn't stop at the median.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: traffic circle at the intersection, and I was well into the circle heading straight through. car coming on my right was coming fast while I was halfway through already. they finally slammed on the brakes and did not hit me, but it did shake me up

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Vehicle parked on south side of street opened door at last second and I collided with door while heading eastbound on 10th Ave. A car had just passed in middle of the lane heading west giving me no room to avoid the door.  Bike was damaged and I went emergency for stitches. Police called and arrived. I believe no points or penalty levied to driver.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver ran through red light heading north on Fraser at full speed (didn't see the red light?!), just missing a person who was crossing the intersection on a green light. Super dangerous, especially with the speed the driver was driving.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Riding westbound on 10th noticed a vehicle following me for several blocks, revving its engine repeatedly. About 1/2 block east of Fraser St., driver revved engine again and started honking horn. Vehicle was unable to pass me, as the street is narrow, with parking on both sides. I consistently ride about 1 metre from parked cars to avoid being doored. Driver rolled down window and yelled "you're not a car!", along with expletives. Just latest of several threatening incidents like this.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Heading east on 10th a car entered the roundabout from Carolina, indicating he was turning on 10th heading east. Fine. But then on the roundabout the car came to an abrupt stop, so I had to slam my brakes to avoid collision. THEN the car started backing up on the roundabout while I was standing right behind him. I started screaming for the car to stop. Luckily it stopped just in time, but I was terrified! I had my bike lights on, aimed at the rearview mirror. Driver just didn't look.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Yellow cab taxi  ran red light right across the 10th ave bike path Tbear miss would have been a t-bone hit not head on). I yelled out of shock and hit my breaks and the taxi slammed on its breaks.  We avoided a collision but I was pretty shaken up.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver didn’t stop at the stop sign and hit the cyclist ahead of me. They didn’t seem too badly injured but they might have had a concussion.

i_type: Fall
details: I was heading with family west bound on the Columbia Trail en-route to Midway Station. I came upon a large bull snake in front to my front tire. I applied both front and back brakes to avoid it,  unfortunately,  applied too much pressure on front brake. I went over the handle bars and landed on my left forearm and head. Fortunately, I had a good helmet on to protect my skull. I proceeded after a few minutes to dust off. Watch for darting harmless sm local snakes in some areas in this section.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A vehicle turned left in front of us from the oncoming lane after waiting a brief period seemingly waiting for us to pass before turning.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Coasting down Chute Lake Rd hill in the bike lane (moving at ~50kph) and vehicle stuck in morning traffic (moving ~5kph) swerved into bike lane to avoid debris in road. Hit brakes so hard that tires locked up and nearly fell as I skidded past driver (who was still taking up most of the bike lane). Driver was oblivious even after the fact.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: parking lot as a whole can be chaotic and hard to navigate- even as a pedestrian

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Truck passed on my left within 45cm of me while I was riding in the lane at 45km/h; there is no bike lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Travelling west on Reekie Rd I signal my intention to take the lane as I will be turning left in 150m at a 4-way stop. A white BMW sedan less than 50m behind me does not change behaviour despite my outstretched left arm and drives passed less than .5 a meter forcing me to veer onto the adjacent gravel pullout.   The near miss occurred about 100m from the intersection with McCulloch Rd.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver passing me intentionally swerved over to scare me. He came within a foot of sideswiping me....

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: This is a 3-way intersection. The vehicle in question had a stop sign. I had the right of way, I had signaled and was in the turning lane. The vehicle proceeded to pull out in front of me causing me to hit the brakes and skid nearly missing riding directly into the passenger side of the vehicle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car came up alongside on my left, very close. Driver then swerved sharply to the right. Passenger then flipped me the middle finger. Car turned on to a side street and came back to the road I was travelling south on. Passenger still giving me the finger. Left road onto a cycle path where the car couldn't follow.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking towards the traffic circle in the middle of the lane, I didn't move over due to ice on the sides and proximity to the traffic circle. Driver sped up and passed me very closely while also swerving into the oncoming lane. Glared at me while passing - it was a punish pass.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Other cyclist riding on wrong side of road because of narrow road and no shoulder. We met on curve

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Path makes an S-curve just before the canal and I did not see the bollard in the path. Swerved just in time to miss it.

i_type: Fall
details: Leaning into a right-hand turn, lost control of the bike owing to contact with a gopher.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver grew impatient with me travelling 30 km/h, I signaled my intent to turn right at the next turn (maybe 2 blocks ahead), rather than waiting he sped up and passed closely.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was biking West up Aperture drive, and an individual in a grey SUV failed to yield when turning right from the parking lot road and pulled right in front of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Be careful! When using the new bike path, it merges onto a triangle where you can push button and wait to cross university. However drivers in lane are merging from Whoop-Up and do not have a clear line of sight until close to intersection.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver was turning right on a red into moderate traffic. He was focused completely on the oncoming traffic and didn't look right until he was finished his turn at which point he saw me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: NA

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Right turning mv on red light,driver only focusing on northbound vehicles on MMDr, not looking for southbound bicycle on regional path that had green light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: MV passed me when insufficent road wideth to do so forcing me to crowd vehicles parked at the curb. The particular stretch of road is designated as playground zone

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing 6th ave, northbound.  "Car A" in the first east bound lane stopped for me and I began to proceed.  "Car B" in the second east bound lane was travelling at full speed, didn't see me, slammed on their brakes and swerved nearly hitting "Car A".  Then a third car swerved around "Car B" to not hit it, and almost hit me as well.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Pickup truck saw me crossing 6th Ave southbound, had plenty room to cross before he would reach the intersection. Driver deliberately sped up and revved his engine, making me have to rush across his lane before he reached me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Approaching a crosswalk on Whoop Up Drive  on ramp from Scenic Drive South bound. Car stopped prematurely for crosswalk and almost got rear ended by truck behind it.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver was West-Bound turning left onto Stafford Drive South.  Possible there was glare but not likely.  Traffic signal turned amber.  I was behind a large SUV and may not have stood out.  Driver of the Monster Truck hit accelerator as soon as light changed amber and nearly hit me broadside.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle stopped at a red light waiting to make a left turn. I started to cross in the cross walk. The driver looked left for oncoming traffic but didn't look back to the left before starting to move and hit me in the side of the rear wheel. The driver left the incident without stopping.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Safely crossing these train tracks requires a cyclist to cross them at a 90 degree angle, which here means turning directly from the shoulder into the driving lane (heading west bound).  Traffic moving in the same direction prevented me from turning into the driving lane to safely cross the tracks.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Often when I pass this intersection, cars coming S on 14 St N do not see me before they pass their yield sign, causing them to enter the intersection while I am in it with right of way.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car  cut the Observatory and Vancouver corner and entered the oncoming left turn lane by about 3 metres without even a hint of slowing down. No eye contact from the driver (who appeared to be a upper middle-aged woman) when I broke hard to avoid getting taken out.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Ford F150 Truck had a yield but I had the right of way. The vehicle screeched to a stop when I passed in front of the truck which is obvious that he did not see me despite a bright orange helmet.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cycling NE-bound in centre of BIKE LANE ("Single File") and just about to make my left signal to turn onto Willow St. at upcoming intersection, as a black truck (LK456*) passed me on the left, exceeding 30 kph speed limit. This street is clearly-designated as the CITY BIKE ROUTE.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver had a YIELD sign. Driver did not yield, nor slow down at this intersection. I wear hi-vis colours. I was very visible. I slammed on my brakes.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding down Third Street. It's in a residential area. As it crosses the Fairview area, Third Street has the right of way and cross streets have stop signs. But drivers on the cross streets often do not fully stop. In this case a car went rolled through  the stop sign and I had to brake hard to avoid broad-siding him.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Was crossing intersection from the right, vehicle was turning right so only looked left. Did not stop at stop sign, only yielded. Pulled into intersection while I was in crosswalk and struck me on bicycle.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Two cyclist with front and rear lights riding east on 18th ave, about to turn north (left) onto 43rd st. Vehicle made a left turn at high speed from 43rd st onto 18th ave. The vehicle cut across the wrong side of the road to compensate for the high rate of speed, very nearly colliding with both cyclists.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: The west side of Blackwolf Blvd. is not aligned with the east side at Uplands Blvd. I arrived at the intersection just before a truck. As I proceeded through the intersection I had to move left to avoid running into the curb on the other side, but the truck did not move left to stay in his lane, and so I nearly hit his door.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A driver in an SUV merged into the bike lane to turn right at the intersection. I was in the bike lane where he merged. He knocked me down between the SUV and the curb.

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Walking my bike through the cross walk, I was 3/4 lanes through when a car blew through the crosswalk in the fourth lane at speed missing my front tire by less then a foot.  The new crosswalk lights were flashing, and all other lanes had stopped. She was oblivious to me, my bike, the crosswalk light

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Illegal right turn by driver from westbound 58 ave to northbound 5 st while the protected northbound cyclist crossing light was on and "no right turn" signs for automobiles lit. This situation happens very frequently with the new "improved" (?) signage but usually I can avoid the illegally right turning vehicle.

i_type: Fall
details: I had decided to use the gravel road from 50th to Sandy Beach, rather than the bike path. I found my lights broken on side of road but don't recall the accident or my walk back home. Later observed there was a bump or ridge in the gravel road followed by a  wet drainage flow. Assuming I hit the bump

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Pickup truck passed me in the intersection to get ahead as I was crossing elbow dr along 50th sw.   Close call, big pickup, very unnerving.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car driving West was speeding trying  to make the green light and passed me very close at high speed as I was crossing elbow drive at the light.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Driver passed me with less than a meter between me and him at 50+kph

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car drove past me, very close, at high speed (est. 70kph) to get to the stop ahead of me.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car traveling down hill way above the speed limit passed me within 1 meter as I was also traveling  down hill... very scary

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Extremely close brush-by from a black truck. Video and more details here: https://twitter.com/itsakev/status/806661841715724288

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A white Calgary Board of Education (CBE) truck with # 67 on it pulled into my lane as it was passing me got as close as possible to me without running me over, then got back into the left lane and continued in the left lane until I lost sight of it.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A CANA Truck sped up to run a red light, putting everyone else on the road at risk. Video evidence of the incident here: https://twitter.com/itsakev/status/819189857452855297

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle passed me while crossing McLeod trail leaving barely centimetres of space while accelerating aggressively.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Heading northbound, I was turning left to head West on 10th by going around the round about. Car approaching southbound did not yield and stopped at last minute, narrowing avoiding a collision with me.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details:
Heading westbound by bike on 10th avenue. Doored by person exiting parked vehicle on north (westbound) side of the street.  I believe right side handlebar contacted door frame, causing loss of control and fall to pavement. Bike unrideable following accident.

This occurred in a section of 10th avenue where the ROW has two parking lanes and one general traffic lane used by bikes and vehicles in both directions. This is a designated neighbourhood bikeway in the City of Vancouver.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A car nearly ran a stale red light - it stopped with all four wheels in the intersection. Caught me off-guard!

i_type: Near collision with stationary object or vehicle
details:
Biking east through the lane,  exiting to cross Guelph St. I checked to see if the street was clear and it was. Then biked across and suddenly a driver in a car came around the corner from Broadway at high speed and braked just before hitting me.
Then honked implying it was my fault.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cycling south bound across intersection, car was readying to turn right from Victoria Dr onto Broadway and did not check for pedestrian or bike traffic. As I neared the sidewalk, car had to hard-stop in the middle of the pedestrian path after I yelled at it to stop.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Northbound Driver on Kingsway ran the red, which was so stale that it was about halfway through the light cycle. They went through in between another eastbound cyclist & us, seeming not to even see the light at all.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was cycling westbound along e. 10th. taxi was traveling in same direction. they turned right without shoulder checking or turning on their blinker. I slowed down anticipating this but still a near miss.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: SUV cutting from one alley to another across the bike path without checking if anyone was coming - drove at high speed perpendicular across path to cut across to Broadway

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was cycling west. I saw the vehicle exiting the parking lot so I slowed down in case the car didn't stop. I rang my bell multiple times to let the driver know that I have the right of way. However, the drivers windows were up and also the driver appeared to be a senior (possibly hard of hearing). Car did not stop until I was yelling at him.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle coming out of Kingsgate mall driveway nearly hit me. Driver stopped just short of hitting me. Design encourages drivers to criss the cycle track without scanning for cyclists first. Fail!

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: In roundabout - car approached into the roundabout, cyclists slowed waiting for the car to stop, I should, but started moving once I was infront of it.

i_type: Fall
details:
I witnessed cyclist crash after hitting a large pile of loose grit & sand in the road.  It was on Ontario, on the north side of the 10th Ave mini-roundabout.

Cyclist suffered serious injuries as a result.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: Person got doored.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A pickup truck going the wrong way on Columbia went through a stop sign and almost hit me broadside. I braked hard to avoid slamming into the truck and flew over the handle bars. I put out my hands to break my fall and broke my scaffoid (wrist) and both radial heads (elbows). Driver charged by ICBC.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Ebike rider was cycling west along 10th avenue. As they approached Alberta street a Toyota minivan heading north ran through the stop sign. Luckily they stopped and did not hit the cyclist.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details:
Car heading westbound tried making a left hand turn in front of me assuming they had enough time. Had to brake really hard and swerve to avoid being hit. 

Driver waived at me. 

10th ave does not have enough room for parking, cars both ways and cyclist both ways.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Vehicle was traveling northbound on Victoria on a green light and proceeded to turn right onto Commercial Drive without any significant reduction in speed, no shoulder check or any acknowledgement that there could have been any pedestrians or cyclists using the designated paths in the intersection. In approaching the intersection, I had to hard-stop because the car did not make any signs of slowing or seeing my presence.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: A cyclist going north on Victoria almost got hit by a car coming southbound on Victoria and turning left onto Broadway.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing Broadway as part of the Central Valley Greenway path.  I was crossing Broadway in the painted bike path.  One car had stopped for me already as I was crossing and then another car appeared in the next lane and we both had to slam on our brakes to avoid colliding.  I fell over.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Waited in bike box in front of cars@ red light. Began pedaling straight ahead (west) on green w/ plan to turn NW onto N Grandview/CVG just after the intersection.Not fully taking the lane (was maybe too far to the right) & car behind tried to squeeze by at high speed for v close pass w/in same lane.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Waiting st SW intersection in bike lane for light change to proceed East across Victoria Dr. A vehicle made a right turn (E to S) from Commercial to Victoria while light still red. Light turned green and bikes/pedestrians started to move, but a second vehicle behind the first did not check for foot/bike traffic and started moving into bikes’ pathway. I yelled and they immediately stopped at an angle, starting to encroach on the painted path.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I’m heading east with a green  light. A driver on Prince Edward going north turned right onto Broadway almost hitting me. He could see me but decided I was less important than his turn.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was riding my bike southbound on Victoria Dr, with the accident occurring between 8th ave and Broadway.  The accident occurred when a driver that was heading northbound on Victoria Dr. turned left, across a solid yellow line, into a backlane, behind the budhist temple.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Car entered bike lane, while I was beside them.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: While riding SW towards Broadway, I attempted a pass of a slow-moving cyclist. I did not ring my bell early enough to signal the pass and only managed to slow down a bit before crashing into the other cyclist that suddenly turned left towards E 6th without any indication. We both remained upright and indicated no injuries.

i_type: Collision with stationary object or vehicle
details: A person in a parked car opened their door into the path of bicyclist on 10th Ave. I'm not sure if the bicyclist actually hit the door, but it definitely caused her to swerve and fall on the ground. Her bike got mangled and an ambulance got called.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Motorist exit alley between broadway and 10th Ave quickly.  Ontario (Northbound) is downhill. Motor pull out of the alley without checking bikes. I believe there should be improved signage or traffic calming devices for motorists exiting the alley. either Eastbound or more specifically Westbound.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing Main St heading eastbound towards Kingsway - I had the green light & a car was turning left from 10th onto Main. Car did not stop or slow down.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Dark and raining at the time. Pedestrian steps out in front of my path. Had to brake hard and swerve around him. I have a bright front light and helmet front lights.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was heading south on Ontario st when I stopped at the 4 way. It was my right of way and so I went but a car to my right ran their red because she did not see me despite my front lights and rear lights being on. The car bent my front fork slightly and I rolled up on to the hood and back off down.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Cycling north. Right at the curb extension on the north east corner. A driver (in a Dodge) went past me very close and very fast.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Biking north down St. Catharines St when pick-up truck exiting alley and turning left cut the corner and turned into me. Vehicle did not stop before proceeding out of alley, driver did not appear to see me until directly head-on with my bike. Driver stopped within one foot of hitting me. Near miss. Was very dark out, but I had a high beam front light on my cargo bike.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: I was crossing with a bike trailer from the west side of the street heading East, when a large white moving truck turned right on red just as I was entering the intersection. He clearly wasn't going to stop so I had to swerve, turn 360 on the road and go back onto the sidewalk.

i_type: Near collision with moving object or vehicle
details: Close call right hook as I attempted to cross Clark avenue on green light.

i_type: Collision with moving object or vehicle
